05重 11:20 Write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates,
05重 11:21 so that your days and the days of your children may be multiplied in the land that the LORD swore to your ancestors to give them, as long as the heavens are above the earth.
05重 11:22 If you will diligently observe this entire commandment that I am commanding you, loving the LORD your God, walking in all his ways, and holding fast to him,
05重 11:23 then the LORD will drive out all these nations before you, and you will dispossess nations larger and mightier than yourselves.
05重 11:24 Every place on which you set foot shall be yours; your territory shall extend from the wilderness to the Lebanon and from the River, the river Euphrates, to the Western Sea.
05重 11:25 No one will be able to stand against you; the LORD your God will put the fear and dread of you on all the land on which you set foot, as he promised you.
05重 11:26 See, I am setting before you today a blessing and a curse:
05重 11:27 the blessing, if you obey the commandments of the LORD your God that I am commanding you today;
05重 11:28 and the curse, if you do not obey the commandments of the LORD your God, but turn from the way that I am commanding you today, to follow other gods that you have not known.
05重 11:29 When the LORD your God has brought you into the land that you are entering to occupy, you shall set the blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal.
05重 11:30 As you know, they are beyond the Jordan, some distance to the west, in the land of the Canaanites who live in the Arabah, opposite Gilgal, beside the oak of Moreh.
05重 11:31 When you cross the Jordan to go in to occupy the land that the LORD your God is giving you, and when you occupy it and live in it,
05重 11:32 you must diligently observe all the statutes and ordinances that I am setting before you today.
05重 12:1 These are the statutes and ordinances that you must diligently observe in the land that the LORD, the God of your ancestors, has given you to occupy all the days that you live on the earth.
05重 12:2 You must demolish completely all the places where the nations whom you are about to dispossess served their gods, on the mountain heights, on the hills, and under every leafy tree.
05重 12:3 Break down their altars, smash their pillars, burn their sacred poles with fire, and hew down the idols of their gods, and thus blot out their name from their places.
05重 12:4 You shall not worship the LORD your God in such ways.
05重 12:5 But you shall seek the place that the LORD your God will choose out of all your tribes as his habitation to put his name there. You shall go there,
05重 12:6 bringing there your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, your tithes and your donations, your votive gifts, your freewill offerings, and the firstlings of your herds and flocks.
05重 12:7 And you shall eat there in the presence of the LORD your God, you and your households together, rejoicing in all the undertakings in which the LORD your God has blessed you.
05重 12:8 You shall not act as we are acting here today, all of us according to our own desires,
05重 12:9 for you have not yet come into the rest and the possession that the LORD your God is giving you.
05重 12:10 When you cross over the Jordan and live in the land that the LORD your God is allotting to you, and when he gives you rest from your enemies all around so that you live in safety,
05重 12:11 then you shall bring everything that I command you to the place that the LORD your God will choose as a dwelling for his name: your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, your tithes and your donations, and all your choice votive gifts that you vow to the LORD.
05重 12:12 And you shall rejoice before the LORD your God, you together with your sons and your daughters, your male and female slaves, and the Levites who reside in your towns (since they have no allotment or inheritance with you).
05重 12:13 Take care that you do not offer your burnt offerings at any place you happen to see.
05重 12:14 But only at the place that the LORD will choose in one of your tribes--there you shall offer your burnt offerings and there you shall do everything I command you.
05重 12:15 Yet whenever you desire you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your towns, according to the blessing that the LORD your God has given you; the unclean and the clean may eat of it, as they would of gazelle or deer.
05重 12:16 The blood, however, you must not eat; you shall pour it out on the ground like water.
05重 12:17 Nor may you eat within your towns the tithe of your grain, your wine, and your oil, the firstlings of your herds and your flocks, any of your votive gifts that you vow, your freewill offerings, or your donations;
05重 12:18 these you shall eat in the presence of the LORD your God at the place that the LORD your God will choose, you together with your son and your daughter, your male and female slaves, and the Levites resident in your towns, rejoicing in the presence of the LORD your God in all your undertakings.
05重 12:19 Take care that you do not neglect the Levite as long as you live in your land.
05重 12:20 When the LORD your God enlarges your territory, as he has promised you, and you say, "I am going to eat some meat," because you wish to eat meat, you may eat meat whenever you have the desire.
05重 12:21 If the place where the LORD your God will choose to put his name is too far from you, and you slaughter as I have commanded you any of your herd or flock that the LORD has given you, then you may eat within your towns whenever you desire.
05重 12:22 Indeed, just as gazelle or deer is eaten, so you may eat it; the unclean and the clean alike may eat it.
05重 12:23 Only be sure that you do not eat the blood; for the blood is the life, and you shall not eat the life with the meat.
05重 12:24 Do not eat it; you shall pour it out on the ground like water.
05重 12:25 Do not eat it, so that all may go well with you and your children after you, because you do what is right in the sight of the LORD.
05重 12:26 But the sacred donations that are due from you, and your votive gifts, you shall bring to the place that the LORD will choose.
05重 12:27 You shall present your burnt offerings, both the meat and the blood, on the altar of the LORD your God; the blood of your other sacrifices shall be poured out beside the altar of the LORD your God, but the meat you may eat.
05重 12:28 Be careful to obey all these words that I command you today, so that it may go well with you and with your children after you forever, because you will be doing what is good and right in the sight of the LORD your God.
05重 12:29 When the LORD your God has cut off before you the nations whom you are about to enter to dispossess them, when you have dispossessed them and live in their land,
05重 12:30 take care that you are not snared into imitating them, after they have been destroyed before you: do not inquire concerning their gods, saying, "How did these nations worship their gods? I also want to do the same."
05重 12:31 You must not do the same for the LORD your God, because every abhorrent thing that the LORD hates they have done for their gods. They would even burn their sons and their daughters in the fire to their gods.
05重 12:32 You must diligently observe everything that I command you; do not add to it or take anything from it.
05重 13:1 If prophets or those who divine by dreams appear among you and promise you omens or portents,
