05重 13:18 if you obey the voice of the LORD your God by keeping all his commandments that I am commanding you today, doing what is right in the sight of the LORD your God.
05重 14:1 You are children of the LORD your God. You must not lacerate yourselves or shave your forelocks for the dead.
05重 14:2 For you are a people holy to the LORD your God; it is you the LORD has chosen out of all the peoples on earth to be his people, his treasured possession.
05重 14:3 You shall not eat any abhorrent thing.
05重 14:4 These are the animals you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat,
05重 14:5 the hart, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex, the antelope, and the mountain-sheep.
05重 14:6 Any animal that divides the hoof and has the hoof cleft in two, and chews the cud, among the animals, you may eat.
05重 14:7 Yet of those that chew the cud or have the hoof cleft you shall not eat these: the camel, the hare, and the rock badger, because they chew the cud but do not divide the hoof; they are unclean for you.
05重 14:8 And the pig, because it divides the hoof but does not chew the cud, is unclean for you. You shall not eat their meat, and you shall not touch their carcasses.
05重 14:9 Of all that live in water you may eat these: whatever has fins and scales you may eat.
05重 14:10 And whatever does not have fins and scales you shall not eat; it is unclean for you.
05重 14:11 You may eat any clean birds.
05重 14:12 But these are the ones that you shall not eat: the eagle, the vulture, the osprey,
05重 14:13 the buzzard, the kite, of any kind;
05重 14:14 every raven of any kind;
05重 14:15 the ostrich, the nighthawk, the sea gull, the hawk, of any kind;
05重 14:16 the little owl and the great owl, the water hen
05重 14:17 and the desert owl, the carrion vulture and the cormorant,
05重 14:18 the stork, the heron, of any kind; the hoopoe and the bat.
05重 14:19 And all winged insects are unclean for you; they shall not be eaten.
05重 14:20 You may eat any clean winged creature.
05重 14:21 You shall not eat anything that dies of itself; you may give it to aliens residing in your towns for them to eat, or you may sell it to a foreigner. For you are a people holy to the LORD your God. You shall not boil a kid in its mother's milk.
05重 14:22 Set apart a tithe of all the yield of your seed that is brought in yearly from the field.
05重 14:23 In the presence of the LORD your God, in the place that he will choose as a dwelling for his name, you shall eat the tithe of your grain, your wine, and your oil, as well as the firstlings of your herd and flock, so that you may learn to fear the LORD your God always.
05重 14:24 But if, when the LORD your God has blessed you, the distance is so great that you are unable to transport it, because the place where the LORD your God will choose to set his name is too far away from you,
05重 14:25 then you may turn it into money. With the money secure in hand, go to the place that the LORD your God will choose;
05重 14:26 spend the money for whatever you wish--oxen, sheep, wine, strong drink, or whatever you desire. And you shall eat there in the presence of the LORD your God, you and your household rejoicing together.
05重 14:27 As for the Levites resident in your towns, do not neglect them, because they have no allotment or inheritance with you.
05重 14:28 Every third year you shall bring out the full tithe of your produce for that year, and store it within your towns;
05重 14:29 the Levites, because they have no allotment or inheritance with you, as well as the resident aliens, the orphans, and the widows in your towns, may come and eat their fill so that the LORD your God may bless you in all the work that you undertake.
05重 15:1 Every seventh year you shall grant a remission of debts.
05重 15:2 And this is the manner of the remission: every creditor shall remit the claim that is held against a neighbor, not exacting it of a neighbor who is a member of the community, because the LORD's remission has been proclaimed.
05重 15:3 Of a foreigner you may exact it, but you must remit your claim on whatever any member of your community owes you.
05重 15:4 There will, however, be no one in need among you, because the LORD is sure to bless you in the land that the LORD your God is giving you as a possession to occupy,
05重 15:5 if only you will obey the LORD your God by diligently observing this entire commandment that I command you today.
05重 15:6 When the LORD your God has blessed you, as he promised you, you will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow; you will rule over many nations, but they will not rule over you.
05重 15:7 If there is among you anyone in need, a member of your community in any of your towns within the land that the LORD your God is giving you, do not be hard-hearted or tight-fisted toward your needy neighbor.
05重 15:8 You should rather open your hand, willingly lending enough to meet the need, whatever it may be.
05重 15:9 Be careful that you do not entertain a mean thought, thinking, "The seventh year, the year of remission, is near," and therefore view your needy neighbor with hostility and give nothing; your neighbor might cry to the LORD against you, and you would incur guilt.
05重 15:10 Give liberally and be ungrudging when you do so, for on this account the LORD your God will bless you in all your work and in all that you undertake.
05重 15:11 Since there will never cease to be some in need on the earth, I therefore command you, "Open your hand to the poor and needy neighbor in your land."
05重 15:12 If a member of your community, whether a Hebrew man or a Hebrew woman, is sold to you and works for you six years, in the seventh year you shall set that person free.
05重 15:13 And when you send a male slave out from you a free person, you shall not send him out empty-handed.
05重 15:14 Provide liberally out of your flock, your threshing floor, and your wine press, thus giving to him some of the bounty with which the LORD your God has blessed you.
05重 15:15 Remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the LORD your God redeemed you; for this reason I lay this command upon you today.
05重 15:16 But if he says to you, "I will not go out from you," because he loves you and your household, since he is well off with you,
05重 15:17 then you shall take an awl and thrust it through his earlobe into the door, and he shall be your slave forever. You shall do the same with regard to your female slave.
05重 15:18 Do not consider it a hardship when you send them out from you free persons, because for six years they have given you services worth the wages of hired laborers; and the LORD your God will bless you in all that you do.
05重 15:19 Every firstling male born of your herd and flock you shall consecrate to the LORD your God; you shall not do work with your firstling ox nor shear the firstling of your flock.
05重 15:20 You shall eat it, you together with your household, in the presence of the LORD your God year by year at the place that the LORD will choose.
05重 15:21 But if it has any defect--any serious defect, such as lameness or blindness--you shall not sacrifice it to the LORD your God;
05重 15:22 within your towns you may eat it, the unclean and the clean alike, as you would a gazelle or deer.
05重 15:23 Its blood, however, you must not eat; you shall pour it out on the ground like water.
05重 16:1 Observe the month of Abib by keeping the passover for the LORD your God, for in the month of Abib the LORD your God brought you out of Egypt by night.
05重 16:2 You shall offer the passover sacrifice for the LORD your God, from the flock and the herd, at the place that the LORD will choose as a dwelling for his name.
05重 16:3 You must not eat with it anything leavened. For seven days you shall eat unleavened bread with it--the bread of affliction--because you came out of the land of Egypt in great haste, so that all the days of your life you may remember the day of your departure from the land of Egypt.
05重 16:4 No leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory for seven days; and none of the meat of what you slaughter on the evening of the first day shall remain until morning.
05重 16:5 You are not permitted to offer the passover sacrifice within any of your towns that the LORD your God is giving you.
05重 16:6 But at the place that the LORD your God will choose as a dwelling for his name, only there shall you offer the passover sacrifice, in the evening at sunset, the time of day when you departed from Egypt.
05重 16:7 You shall cook it and eat it at the place that the LORD your God will choose; the next morning you may go back to your tents.
05重 16:8 For six days you shall continue to eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a solemn assembly for the LORD your God, when you shall do no work.
05重 16:9 You shall count seven weeks; begin to count the seven weeks from the time the sickle is first put to the standing grain.
05重 16:10 Then you shall keep the festival of weeks for the LORD your God, contributing a freewill offering in proportion to the blessing that you have received from the LORD your God.
05重 16:11 Rejoice before the LORD your God--you and your sons and your daughters, your male and female slaves, the Levites resident in your towns, as well as the strangers, the orphans, and the widows who are among you--at the place that the LORD your God will choose as a dwelling for his name.
05重 16:12 Remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and diligently observe these statutes.
05重 16:13 You shall keep the festival of booths for seven days, when you have gathered in the produce from your threshing floor and your wine press.
05重 16:14 Rejoice during your festival, you and your sons and your daughters, your male and female slaves, as well as the Levites, the strangers, the orphans, and the widows resident in your towns.
05重 16:15 Seven days you shall keep the festival for the LORD your God at the place that the LORD will choose; for the LORD your God will bless you in all your produce and in all your undertakings, and you shall surely celebrate.
05重 16:16 Three times a year all your males shall appear before the LORD your God at the place that he will choose: at the festival of unleavened bread, at the festival of weeks, and at the festival of booths. They shall not appear before the LORD empty-handed;
05重 16:17 all shall give as they are able, according to the blessing of the LORD your God that he has given you.
05重 16:18 You shall appoint judges and officials throughout your tribes, in all your towns that the LORD your God is giving you, and they shall render just decisions for the people.
05重 16:19 You must not distort justice; you must not show partiality; and you must not accept bribes, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and subverts the cause of those who are in the right.
05重 16:20 Justice, and only justice, you shall pursue, so that you may live and occupy the land that the LORD your God is giving you.
05重 16:21 You shall not plant any tree as a sacred pole beside the altar that you make for the LORD your God;
05重 16:22 nor shall you set up a stone pillar--things that the LORD your God hates.
05重 17:1 You must not sacrifice to the LORD your God an ox or a sheep that has a defect, anything seriously wrong; for that is abhorrent to the LORD your God.
05重 17:2 If there is found among you, in one of your towns that the LORD your God is giving you, a man or woman who does what is evil in the sight of the LORD your God, and transgresses his covenant
05重 17:3 by going to serve other gods and worshiping them--whether the sun or the moon or any of the host of heaven, which I have forbidden--
05重 17:4 and if it is reported to you or you hear of it, and you make a thorough inquiry, and the charge is proved true that such an abhorrent thing has occurred in Israel,
05重 17:5 then you shall bring out to your gates that man or that woman who has committed this crime and you shall stone the man or woman to death.
05重 17:6 On the evidence of two or three witnesses the death sentence shall be executed; a person must not be put to death on the evidence of only one witness.
05重 17:7 The hands of the witnesses shall be the first raised against the person to execute the death penalty, and afterward the hands of all the people. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.
05重 17:8 If a judicial decision is too difficult for you to make between one kind of bloodshed and another, one kind of legal right and another, or one kind of assault and another--any such matters of dispute in your towns--then you shall immediately go up to the place that the LORD your God will choose,
05重 17:9 where you shall consult with the levitical priests and the judge who is in office in those days; they shall announce to you the decision in the case.
05重 17:10 Carry out exactly the decision that they announce to you from the place that the LORD will choose, diligently observing everything they instruct you.
05重 17:11 You must carry out fully the law that they interpret for you or the ruling that they announce to you; do not turn aside from the decision that they announce to you, either to the right or to the left.
05重 17:12 As for anyone who presumes to disobey the priest appointed to minister there to the LORD your God, or the judge, that person shall die. So you shall purge the evil from Israel.
05重 17:13 All the people will hear and be afraid, and will not act presumptuously again.
05重 17:14 When you have come into the land that the LORD your God is giving you, and have taken possession of it and settled in it, and you say, "I will set a king over me, like all the nations that are around me,"
05重 17:15 you may indeed set over you a king whom the LORD your God will choose. One of your own community you may set as king over you; you are not permitted to put a foreigner over you, who is not of your own community.
05重 17:16 Even so, he must not acquire many horses for himself, or return the people to Egypt in order to acquire more horses, since the LORD has said to you, "You must never return that way again."
05重 17:17 And he must not acquire many wives for himself, or else his heart will turn away; also silver and gold he must not acquire in great quantity for himself.
05重 17:18 When he has taken the throne of his kingdom, he shall have a copy of this law written for him in the presence of the levitical priests.
05重 17:19 It shall remain with him and he shall read in it all the days of his life, so that he may learn to fear the LORD his God, diligently observing all the words of this law and these statutes,
05重 17:20 neither exalting himself above other members of the community nor turning aside from the commandment, either to the right or to the left, so that he and his descendants may reign long over his kingdom in Israel.
05重 18:1 The levitical priests, the whole tribe of Levi, shall have no allotment or inheritance within Israel. They may eat the sacrifices that are the LORD's portion
05重 18:2 but they shall have no inheritance among the other members of the community; the LORD is their inheritance, as he promised them.
05重 18:3 This shall be the priests' due from the people, from those offering a sacrifice, whether an ox or a sheep: they shall give to the priest the shoulder, the two jowls, and the stomach.
05重 18:4 The first fruits of your grain, your wine, and your oil, as well as the first of the fleece of your sheep, you shall give him.
05重 18:5 For the LORD your God has chosen Levi out of all your tribes, to stand and minister in the name of the LORD, him and his sons for all time.
05重 18:6 If a Levite leaves any of your towns, from wherever he has been residing in Israel, and comes to the place that the LORD will choose (and he may come whenever he wishes),
05重 18:7 then he may minister in the name of the LORD his God, like all his fellow-Levites who stand to minister there before the LORD.
05重 18:8 They shall have equal portions to eat, even though they have income from the sale of family possessions.
05重 18:9 When you come into the land that the LORD your God is giving you, you must not learn to imitate the abhorrent practices of those nations.
05重 18:10 No one shall be found among you who makes a son or daughter pass through fire, or who practices divination, or is a soothsayer, or an augur, or a sorcerer,
05重 18:11 or one who casts spells, or who consults ghosts or spirits, or who seeks oracles from the dead.
05重 18:12 For whoever does these things is abhorrent to the LORD; it is because of such abhorrent practices that the LORD your God is driving them out before you.
05重 18:13 You must remain completely loyal to the LORD your God.
05重 18:14 Although these nations that you are about to dispossess do give heed to soothsayers and diviners, as for you, the LORD your God does not permit you to do so.
05重 18:15 The LORD your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among your own people; you shall heed such a prophet.
05重 18:16 This is what you requested of the LORD your God at Horeb on the day of the assembly when you said: "If I hear the voice of the LORD my God any more, or ever again see this great fire, I will die."
05重 18:17 Then the LORD replied to me: "They are right in what they have said.
05重 18:18 I will raise up for them a prophet like you from among their own people; I will put my words in the mouth of the prophet, who shall speak to them everything that I command.
05重 18:19 Anyone who does not heed the words that the prophet shall speak in my name, I myself will hold accountable.
05重 18:20 But any prophet who speaks in the name of other gods, or who presumes to speak in my name a word that I have not commanded the prophet to speak--that prophet shall die."
05重 18:21 You may say to yourself, "How can we recognize a word that the LORD has not spoken?"
05重 18:22 If a prophet speaks in the name of the LORD but the thing does not take place or prove true, it is a word that the LORD has not spoken. The prophet has spoken it presumptuously; do not be frightened by it.
05重 19:1 When the LORD your God has cut off the nations whose land the LORD your God is giving you, and you have dispossessed them and settled in their towns and in their houses,
05重 19:2 you shall set apart three cities in the land that the LORD your God is giving you to possess.
05重 19:3 You shall calculate the distances and divide into three regions the land that the LORD your God gives you as a possession, so that any homicide can flee to one of them.
05重 19:4 Now this is the case of a homicide who might flee there and live, that is, someone who has killed another person unintentionally when the two had not been at enmity before:
05重 19:5 Suppose someone goes into the forest with another to cut wood, and when one of them swings the ax to cut down a tree, the head slips from the handle and strikes the other person who then dies; the killer may flee to one of these cities and live.
05重 19:6 But if the distance is too great, the avenger of blood in hot anger might pursue and overtake and put the killer to death, although a death sentence was not deserved, since the two had not been at enmity before.
05重 19:7 Therefore I command you: You shall set apart three cities.
05重 19:8 If the LORD your God enlarges your territory, as he swore to your ancestors--and he will give you all the land that he promised your ancestors to give you,
05重 19:9 provided you diligently observe this entire commandment that I command you today, by loving the LORD your God and walking always in his ways--then you shall add three more cities to these three,
05重 19:10 so that the blood of an innocent person may not be shed in the land that the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance, thereby bringing bloodguilt upon you.
05重 19:11 But if someone at enmity with another lies in wait and attacks and takes the life of that person, and flees into one of these cities,
05重 19:12 then the elders of the killer's city shall send to have the culprit taken from there and handed over to the avenger of blood to be put to death.
05重 19:13 Show no pity; you shall purge the guilt of innocent blood from Israel, so that it may go well with you.
05重 19:14 You must not move your neighbor's boundary marker, set up by former generations, on the property that will be allotted to you in the land that the LORD your God is giving you to possess.
05重 19:15 A single witness shall not suffice to convict a person of any crime or wrongdoing in connection with any offense that may be committed. Only on the evidence of two or three witnesses shall a charge be sustained.
05重 19:16 If a malicious witness comes forward to accuse someone of wrongdoing,
05重 19:17 then both parties to the dispute shall appear before the LORD, before the priests and the judges who are in office in those days,
05重 19:18 and the judges shall make a thorough inquiry. If the witness is a false witness, having testified falsely against another,
05重 19:19 then you shall do to the false witness just as the false witness had meant to do to the other. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.
05重 19:20 The rest shall hear and be afraid, and a crime such as this shall never again be committed among you.
05重 19:21 Show no pity: life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.
05重 20:1 When you go out to war against your enemies, and see horses and chariots, an army larger than your own, you shall not be afraid of them; for the LORD your God is with you, who brought you up from the land of Egypt.
05重 20:2 Before you engage in battle, the priest shall come forward and speak to the troops,
05重 20:3 and shall say to them: "Hear, O Israel! Today you are drawing near to do battle against your enemies. Do not lose heart, or be afraid, or panic, or be in dread of them;
05重 20:4 for it is the LORD your God who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to give you victory."
05重 20:5 Then the officials shall address the troops, saying, "Has anyone built a new house but not dedicated it? He should go back to his house, or he might die in the battle and another dedicate it.
05重 20:6 Has anyone planted a vineyard but not yet enjoyed its fruit? He should go back to his house, or he might die in the battle and another be first to enjoy its fruit.
05重 20:7 Has anyone become engaged to a woman but not yet married her? He should go back to his house, or he might die in the battle and another marry her."
05重 20:8 The officials shall continue to address the troops, saying, "Is anyone afraid or disheartened? He should go back to his house, or he might cause the heart of his comrades to melt like his own."
05重 20:9 When the officials have finished addressing the troops, then the commanders shall take charge of them.
05重 20:10 When you draw near to a town to fight against it, offer it terms of peace.
05重 20:11 If it accepts your terms of peace and surrenders to you, then all the people in it shall serve you at forced labor.
05重 20:12 If it does not submit to you peacefully, but makes war against you, then you shall besiege it;
05重 20:13 and when the LORD your God gives it into your hand, you shall put all its males to the sword.
05重 20:14 You may, however, take as your booty the women, the children, livestock, and everything else in the town, all its spoil. You may enjoy the spoil of your enemies, which the LORD your God has given you.
05重 20:15 Thus you shall treat all the towns that are very far from you, which are not towns of the nations here.
05重 20:16 But as for the towns of these peoples that the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance, you must not let anything that breathes remain alive.
05重 20:17 You shall annihilate them--the Hittites and the Amorites, the Canaanites and the Perizzites, the Hivites and the Jebusites--just as the LORD your God has commanded,
05重 20:18 so that they may not teach you to do all the abhorrent things that they do for their gods, and you thus sin against the LORD your God.
05重 20:19 If you besiege a town for a long time, making war against it in order to take it, you must not destroy its trees by wielding an ax against them. Although you may take food from them, you must not cut them down. Are trees in the field human beings that they should come under siege from you?
05重 20:20 You may destroy only the trees that you know do not produce food; you may cut them down for use in building siegeworks against the town that makes war with you, until it falls.
05重 21:1 If, in the land that the LORD your God is giving you to possess, a body is found lying in open country, and it is not known who struck the person down,
05重 21:2 then your elders and your judges shall come out to measure the distances to the towns that are near the body.
05重 21:3 The elders of the town nearest the body shall take a heifer that has never been worked, one that has not pulled in the yoke;
05重 21:4 the elders of that town shall bring the heifer down to a wadi with running water, which is neither plowed nor sown, and shall break the heifer's neck there in the wadi.
05重 21:5 Then the priests, the sons of Levi, shall come forward, for the LORD your God has chosen them to minister to him and to pronounce blessings in the name of the LORD, and by their decision all cases of dispute and assault shall be settled.
05重 21:6 All the elders of that town nearest the body shall wash their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the wadi,
05重 21:7 and they shall declare: "Our hands did not shed this blood, nor were we witnesses to it.
05重 21:8 Absolve, O LORD, your people Israel, whom you redeemed; do not let the guilt of innocent blood remain in the midst of your people Israel." Then they will be absolved of bloodguilt.
05重 21:9 So you shall purge the guilt of innocent blood from your midst, because you must do what is right in the sight of the LORD.
05重 21:10 When you go out to war against your enemies, and the LORD your God hands them over to you and you take them captive,
05重 21:11 suppose you see among the captives a beautiful woman whom you desire and want to marry,
05重 21:12 and so you bring her home to your house: she shall shave her head, pare her nails,
05重 21:13 discard her captive's garb, and shall remain in your house a full month, mourning for her father and mother; after that you may go in to her and be her husband, and she shall be your wife.
05重 21:14 But if you are not satisfied with her, you shall let her go free and not sell her for money. You must not treat her as a slave, since you have dishonored her.
05重 21:15 If a man has two wives, one of them loved and the other disliked, and if both the loved and the disliked have borne him sons, the firstborn being the son of the one who is disliked,
05重 21:16 then on the day when he wills his possessions to his sons, he is not permitted to treat the son of the loved as the firstborn in preference to the son of the disliked, who is the firstborn.
05重 21:17 He must acknowledge as firstborn the son of the one who is disliked, giving him a double portion of all that he has; since he is the first issue of his virility, the right of the firstborn is his.
05重 21:18 If someone has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey his father and mother, who does not heed them when they discipline him,
05重 21:19 then his father and his mother shall take hold of him and bring him out to the elders of his town at the gate of that place.
05重 21:20 They shall say to the elders of his town, "This son of ours is stubborn and rebellious. He will not obey us. He is a glutton and a drunkard."
05重 21:21 Then all the men of the town shall stone him to death. So you shall purge the evil from your midst; and all Israel will hear, and be afraid.
05重 21:22 When someone is convicted of a crime punishable by death and is executed, and you hang him on a tree,
05重 21:23 his corpse must not remain all night upon the tree; you shall bury him that same day, for anyone hung on a tree is under God's curse. You must not defile the land that the LORD your God is giving you for possession.
05重 22:1 You shall not watch your neighbor's ox or sheep straying away and ignore them; you shall take them back to their owner.
05重 22:2 If the owner does not reside near you or you do not know who the owner is, you shall bring it to your own house, and it shall remain with you until the owner claims it; then you shall return it.
05重 22:3 You shall do the same with a neighbor's donkey; you shall do the same with a neighbor's garment; and you shall do the same with anything else that your neighbor loses and you find. You may not withhold your help.
05重 22:4 You shall not see your neighbor's donkey or ox fallen on the road and ignore it; you shall help to lift it up.
05重 22:5 A woman shall not wear a man's apparel, nor shall a man put on a woman's garment; for whoever does such things is abhorrent to the LORD your God.
05重 22:6 If you come on a bird's nest, in any tree or on the ground, with fledglings or eggs, with the mother sitting on the fledglings or on the eggs, you shall not take the mother with the young.
05重 22:7 Let the mother go, taking only the young for yourself, in order that it may go well with you and you may live long.
05重 22:8 When you build a new house, you shall make a parapet for your roof; otherwise you might have bloodguilt on your house, if anyone should fall from it.
05重 22:9 You shall not sow your vineyard with a second kind of seed, or the whole yield will have to be forfeited, both the crop that you have sown and the yield of the vineyard itself.
05重 22:10 You shall not plow with an ox and a donkey yoked together.
05重 22:11 You shall not wear clothes made of wool and linen woven together.
05重 22:12 You shall make tassels on the four corners of the cloak with which you cover yourself.
05重 22:13 Suppose a man marries a woman, but after going in to her, he dislikes her
05重 22:14 and makes up charges against her, slandering her by saying, "I married this woman; but when I lay with her, I did not find evidence of her virginity."
05重 22:15 The father of the young woman and her mother shall then submit the evidence of the young woman's virginity to the elders of the city at the gate.
05重 22:16 The father of the young woman shall say to the elders: "I gave my daughter in marriage to this man but he dislikes her;
05重 22:17 now he has made up charges against her, saying, 'I did not find evidence of your daughter's virginity.' But here is the evidence of my daughter's virginity." Then they shall spread out the cloth before the elders of the town.
05重 22:18 The elders of that town shall take the man and punish him;
05重 22:19 they shall fine him one hundred shekels of silver (which they shall give to the young woman's father) because he has slandered a virgin of Israel. She shall remain his wife; he shall not be permitted to divorce her as long as he lives.
05重 22:20 If, however, this charge is true, that evidence of the young woman's virginity was not found,
05重 22:21 then they shall bring the young woman out to the entrance of her father's house and the men of her town shall stone her to death, because she committed a disgraceful act in Israel by prostituting herself in her father's house. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.
05重 22:22 If a man is caught lying with the wife of another man, both of them shall die, the man who lay with the woman as well as the woman. So you shall purge the evil from Israel.
05重 22:23 If there is a young woman, a virgin already engaged to be married, and a man meets her in the town and lies with her,
05重 22:24 you shall bring both of them to the gate of that town and stone them to death, the young woman because she did not cry for help in the town and the man because he violated his neighbor's wife. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.
05重 22:25 But if the man meets the engaged woman in the open country, and the man seizes her and lies with her, then only the man who lay with her shall die.
05重 22:26 You shall do nothing to the young woman; the young woman has not committed an offense punishable by death, because this case is like that of someone who attacks and murders a neighbor.
05重 22:27 Since he found her in the open country, the engaged woman may have cried for help, but there was no one to rescue her.
05重 22:28 If a man meets a virgin who is not engaged, and seizes her and lies with her, and they are caught in the act,
05重 22:29 the man who lay with her shall give fifty shekels of silver to the young woman's father, and she shall become his wife. Because he violated her he shall not be permitted to divorce her as long as he lives.
05重 22:30 A man shall not marry his father's wife, thereby violating his father's rights.
05重 23:1 No one whose testicles are crushed or whose penis is cut off shall be admitted to the assembly of the LORD.
05重 23:2 Those born of an illicit union shall not be admitted to the assembly of the LORD. Even to the tenth generation, none of their descendants shall be admitted to the assembly of the LORD.
05重 23:3 No Ammonite or Moabite shall be admitted to the assembly of the LORD. Even to the tenth generation, none of their descendants shall be admitted to the assembly of the LORD,
05重 23:4 because they did not meet you with food and water on your journey out of Egypt, and because they hired against you Balaam son of Beor, from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you.
05重 23:5 (Yet the LORD your God refused to heed Balaam; the LORD your God turned the curse into a blessing for you, because the LORD your God loved you.)
05重 23:6 You shall never promote their welfare or their prosperity as long as you live.
05重 23:7 You shall not abhor any of the Edomites, for they are your kin. You shall not abhor any of the Egyptians, because you were an alien residing in their land.
05重 23:8 The children of the third generation that are born to them may be admitted to the assembly of the LORD.
05重 23:9 When you are encamped against your enemies you shall guard against any impropriety.
05重 23:10 If one of you becomes unclean because of a nocturnal emission, then he shall go outside the camp; he must not come within the camp.
05重 23:11 When evening comes, he shall wash himself with water, and when the sun has set, he may come back into the camp.
05重 23:12 You shall have a designated area outside the camp to which you shall go.
05重 23:13 With your utensils you shall have a trowel; when you relieve yourself outside, you shall dig a hole with it and then cover up your excrement.
05重 23:14 Because the LORD your God travels along with your camp, to save you and to hand over your enemies to you, therefore your camp must be holy, so that he may not see anything indecent among you and turn away from you.
05重 23:15 Slaves who have escaped to you from their owners shall not be given back to them.
05重 23:16 They shall reside with you, in your midst, in any place they choose in any one of your towns, wherever they please; you shall not oppress them.
05重 23:17 None of the daughters of Israel shall be a temple prostitute; none of the sons of Israel shall be a temple prostitute.
05重 23:18 You shall not bring the fee of a prostitute or the wages of a male prostitute into the house of the LORD your God in payment for any vow, for both of these are abhorrent to the LORD your God.
05重 23:19 You shall not charge interest on loans to another Israelite, interest on money, interest on provisions, interest on anything that is lent.
05重 23:20 On loans to a foreigner you may charge interest, but on loans to another Israelite you may not charge interest, so that the LORD your God may bless you in all your undertakings in the land that you are about to enter and possess.
05重 23:21 If you make a vow to the LORD your God, do not postpone fulfilling it; for the LORD your God will surely require it of you, and you would incur guilt.
05重 23:22 But if you refrain from vowing, you will not incur guilt.
05重 23:23 Whatever your lips utter you must diligently perform, just as you have freely vowed to the LORD your God with your own mouth.
05重 23:24 If you go into your neighbor's vineyard, you may eat your fill of grapes, as many as you wish, but you shall not put any in a container.
05重 23:25 If you go into your neighbor's standing grain, you may pluck the ears with your hand, but you shall not put a sickle to your neighbor's standing grain.
05重 24:1 Suppose a man enters into marriage with a woman, but she does not please him because he finds something objectionable about her, and so he writes her a certificate of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his house; she then leaves his house
05重 24:2 and goes off to become another man's wife.
05重 24:3 Then suppose the second man dislikes her, writes her a bill of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his house (or the second man who married her dies);
05重 24:4 her first husband, who sent her away, is not permitted to take her again to be his wife after she has been defiled; for that would be abhorrent to the LORD, and you shall not bring guilt on the land that the LORD your God is giving you as a possession.
05重 24:5 When a man is newly married, he shall not go out with the army or be charged with any related duty. He shall be free at home one year, to be happy with the wife whom he has married.
05重 24:6 No one shall take a mill or an upper millstone in pledge, for that would be taking a life in pledge.
05重 24:7 If someone is caught kidnaping another Israelite, enslaving or selling the Israelite, then that kidnaper shall die. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.
05重 24:8 Guard against an outbreak of a leprous skin disease by being very careful; you shall carefully observe whatever the levitical priests instruct you, just as I have commanded them.
05重 24:9 Remember what the LORD your God did to Miriam on your journey out of Egypt.
05重 24:10 When you make your neighbor a loan of any kind, you shall not go into the house to take the pledge.
05重 24:11 You shall wait outside, while the person to whom you are making the loan brings the pledge out to you.
05重 24:12 If the person is poor, you shall not sleep in the garment given you as the pledge.
05重 24:13 You shall give the pledge back by sunset, so that your neighbor may sleep in the cloak and bless you; and it will be to your credit before the LORD your God.
05重 24:14 You shall not withhold the wages of poor and needy laborers, whether other Israelites or aliens who reside in your land in one of your towns.
05重 24:15 You shall pay them their wages daily before sunset, because they are poor and their livelihood depends on them; otherwise they might cry to the LORD against you, and you would incur guilt.
05重 24:16 Parents shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall children be put to death for their parents; only for their own crimes may persons be put to death.
05重 24:17 You shall not deprive a resident alien or an orphan of justice; you shall not take a widow's garment in pledge.
05重 24:18 Remember that you were a slave in Egypt and the LORD your God redeemed you from there; therefore I command you to do this.
05重 24:19 When you reap your harvest in your field and forget a sheaf in the field, you shall not go back to get it; it shall be left for the alien, the orphan, and the widow, so that the LORD your God may bless you in all your undertakings.
05重 24:20 When you beat your olive trees, do not strip what is left; it shall be for the alien, the orphan, and the widow.
05重 24:21 When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, do not glean what is left; it shall be for the alien, the orphan, and the widow.
05重 24:22 Remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt; therefore I am commanding you to do this.
05重 25:1 Suppose two persons have a dispute and enter into litigation, and the judges decide between them, declaring one to be in the right and the other to be in the wrong.
05重 25:2 If the one in the wrong deserves to be flogged, the judge shall make that person lie down and be beaten in his presence with the number of lashes proportionate to the offense.
05重 25:3 Forty lashes may be given but not more; if more lashes than these are given, your neighbor will be degraded in your sight.
05重 25:4 You shall not muzzle an ox while it is treading out the grain.
05重 25:5 When brothers reside together, and one of them dies and has no son, the wife of the deceased shall not be married outside the family to a stranger. Her husband's brother shall go in to her, taking her in marriage, and performing the duty of a husband's brother to her,
05重 25:6 and the firstborn whom she bears shall succeed to the name of the deceased brother, so that his name may not be blotted out of Israel.
05重 25:7 But if the man has no desire to marry his brother's widow, then his brother's widow shall go up to the elders at the gate and say, "My husband's brother refuses to perpetuate his brother's name in Israel; he will not perform the duty of a husband's brother to me."
05重 25:8 Then the elders of his town shall summon him and speak to him. If he persists, saying, "I have no desire to marry her,"
05重 25:9 then his brother's wife shall go up to him in the presence of the elders, pull his sandal off his foot, spit in his face, and declare, "This is what is done to the man who does not build up his brother's house."
05重 25:10 Throughout Israel his family shall be known as "the house of him whose sandal was pulled off."
05重 25:11 If men get into a fight with one another, and the wife of one intervenes to rescue her husband from the grip of his opponent by reaching out and seizing his genitals,
05重 25:12 you shall cut off her hand; show no pity.
05重 25:13 You shall not have in your bag two kinds of weights, large and small.
05重 25:14 You shall not have in your house two kinds of measures, large and small.
05重 25:15 You shall have only a full and honest weight; you shall have only a full and honest measure, so that your days may be long in the land that the LORD your God is giving you.
05重 25:16 For all who do such things, all who act dishonestly, are abhorrent to the LORD your God.
05重 25:17 Remember what Amalek did to you on your journey out of Egypt,
05重 25:18 how he attacked you on the way, when you were faint and weary, and struck down all who lagged behind you; he did not fear God.
05重 25:19 Therefore when the LORD your God has given you rest from all your enemies on every hand, in the land that the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance to possess, you shall blot out the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven; do not forget.
05重 26:1 When you have come into the land that the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance to possess, and you possess it, and settle in it,
05重 26:2 you shall take some of the first of all the fruit of the ground, which you harvest from the land that the LORD your God is giving you, and you shall put it in a basket and go to the place that the LORD your God will choose as a dwelling for his name.
05重 26:3 You shall go to the priest who is in office at that time, and say to him, "Today I declare to the LORD your God that I have come into the land that the LORD swore to our ancestors to give us."
05重 26:4 When the priest takes the basket from your hand and sets it down before the altar of the LORD your God,
05重 26:5 you shall make this response before the LORD your God: "A wandering Aramean was my ancestor; he went down into Egypt and lived there as an alien, few in number, and there he became a great nation, mighty and populous.
05重 26:6 When the Egyptians treated us harshly and afflicted us, by imposing hard labor on us,
05重 26:7 we cried to the LORD, the God of our ancestors; the LORD heard our voice and saw our affliction, our toil, and our oppression.
05重 26:8 The LORD brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm, with a terrifying display of power, and with signs and wonders;
05重 26:9 and he brought us into this place and gave us this land, a land flowing with milk and honey.
05重 26:10 So now I bring the first of the fruit of the ground that you, O LORD, have given me." You shall set it down before the LORD your God and bow down before the LORD your God.
05重 26:11 Then you, together with the Levites and the aliens who reside among you, shall celebrate with all the bounty that the LORD your God has given to you and to your house.
05重 26:12 When you have finished paying all the tithe of your produce in the third year (which is the year of the tithe), giving it to the Levites, the aliens, the orphans, and the widows, so that they may eat their fill within your towns,
05重 26:13 then you shall say before the LORD your God: "I have removed the sacred portion from the house, and I have given it to the Levites, the resident aliens, the orphans, and the widows, in accordance with your entire commandment that you commanded me; I have neither transgressed nor forgotten any of your commandments:
05重 26:14 I have not eaten of it while in mourning; I have not removed any of it while I was unclean; and I have not offered any of it to the dead. I have obeyed the LORD my God, doing just as you commanded me.
05重 26:15 Look down from your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless your people Israel and the ground that you have given us, as you swore to our ancestors--a land flowing with milk and honey."
05重 26:16 This very day the LORD your God is commanding you to observe these statutes and ordinances; so observe them diligently with all your heart and with all your soul.
05重 26:17 Today you have obtained the LORD's agreement: to be your God; and for you to walk in his ways, to keep his statutes, his commandments, and his ordinances, and to obey him.
05重 26:18 Today the LORD has obtained your agreement: to be his treasured people, as he promised you, and to keep his commandments;
05重 26:19 for him to set you high above all nations that he has made, in praise and in fame and in honor; and for you to be a people holy to the LORD your God, as he promised.
05重 27:1 Then Moses and the elders of Israel charged all the people as follows: Keep the entire commandment that I am commanding you today.
05重 27:2 On the day that you cross over the Jordan into the land that the LORD your God is giving you, you shall set up large stones and cover them with plaster.
05重 27:3 You shall write on them all the words of this law when you have crossed over, to enter the land that the LORD your God is giving you, a land flowing with milk and honey, as the LORD, the God of your ancestors, promised you.
05重 27:4 So when you have crossed over the Jordan, you shall set up these stones, about which I am commanding you today, on Mount Ebal, and you shall cover them with plaster.
05重 27:5 And you shall build an altar there to the LORD your God, an altar of stones on which you have not used an iron tool.
05重 27:6 You must build the altar of the LORD your God of unhewn stones. Then offer up burnt offerings on it to the LORD your God,
05重 27:7 make sacrifices of well-being, and eat them there, rejoicing before the LORD your God.
05重 27:8 You shall write on the stones all the words of this law very clearly.
05重 27:9 Then Moses and the levitical priests spoke to all Israel, saying: Keep silence and hear, O Israel! This very day you have become the people of the LORD your God.
05重 27:10 Therefore obey the LORD your God, observing his commandments and his statutes that I am commanding you today.
05重 27:11 The same day Moses charged the people as follows:
05重 27:12 When you have crossed over the Jordan, these shall stand on Mount Gerizim for the blessing of the people: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin.
05重 27:13 And these shall stand on Mount Ebal for the curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.
05重 27:14 Then the Levites shall declare in a loud voice to all the Israelites:
05重 27:15 "Cursed be anyone who makes an idol or casts an image, anything abhorrent to the LORD, the work of an artisan, and sets it up in secret." All the people shall respond, saying, "Amen!"
05重 27:16 "Cursed be anyone who dishonors father or mother." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:17 "Cursed be anyone who moves a neighbor's boundary marker." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:18 "Cursed be anyone who misleads a blind person on the road." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:19 "Cursed be anyone who deprives the alien, the orphan, and the widow of justice." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:20 "Cursed be anyone who lies with his father's wife, because he has violated his father's rights." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:21 "Cursed be anyone who lies with any animal." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:22 "Cursed be anyone who lies with his sister, whether the daughter of his father or the daughter of his mother." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:23 "Cursed be anyone who lies with his mother-in-law." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:24 "Cursed be anyone who strikes down a neighbor in secret." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:25 "Cursed be anyone who takes a bribe to shed innocent blood." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 27:26 "Cursed be anyone who does not uphold the words of this law by observing them." All the people shall say, "Amen!"
05重 28:1 If you will only obey the LORD your God, by diligently observing all his commandments that I am commanding you today, the LORD your God will set you high above all the nations of the earth;
05重 28:2 all these blessings shall come upon you and overtake you, if you obey the LORD your God:
05重 28:3 Blessed shall you be in the city, and blessed shall you be in the field.
05重 28:4 Blessed shall be the fruit of your womb, the fruit of your ground, and the fruit of your livestock, both the increase of your cattle and the issue of your flock.
05重 28:5 Blessed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl.
05重 28:6 Blessed shall you be when you come in, and blessed shall you be when you go out.
05重 28:7 The LORD will cause your enemies who rise against you to be defeated before you; they shall come out against you one way, and flee before you seven ways.
05重 28:8 The LORD will command the blessing upon you in your barns, and in all that you undertake; he will bless you in the land that the LORD your God is giving you.
05重 28:9 The LORD will establish you as his holy people, as he has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the LORD your God and walk in his ways.
05重 28:10 All the peoples of the earth shall see that you are called by the name of the LORD, and they shall be afraid of you.
05重 28:11 The LORD will make you abound in prosperity, in the fruit of your womb, in the fruit of your livestock, and in the fruit of your ground in the land that the LORD swore to your ancestors to give you.
05重 28:12 The LORD will open for you his rich storehouse, the heavens, to give the rain of your land in its season and to bless all your undertakings. You will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow.
05重 28:13 The LORD will make you the head, and not the tail; you shall be only at the top, and not at the bottom--if you obey the commandments of the LORD your God, which I am commanding you today, by diligently observing them,
05重 28:14 and if you do not turn aside from any of the words that I am commanding you today, either to the right or to the left, following other gods to serve them.
05重 28:15 But if you will not obey the LORD your God by diligently observing all his commandments and decrees, which I am commanding you today, then all these curses shall come upon you and overtake you:
05重 28:16 Cursed shall you be in the city, and cursed shall you be in the field.
05重 28:17 Cursed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl.
05重 28:18 Cursed shall be the fruit of your womb, the fruit of your ground, the increase of your cattle and the issue of your flock.
05重 28:19 Cursed shall you be when you come in, and cursed shall you be when you go out.
05重 28:20 The LORD will send upon you disaster, panic, and frustration in everything you attempt to do, until you are destroyed and perish quickly, on account of the evil of your deeds, because you have forsaken me.
05重 28:21 The LORD will make the pestilence cling to you until it has consumed you off the land that you are entering to possess.
05重 28:22 The LORD will afflict you with consumption, fever, inflammation, with fiery heat and drought, and with blight and mildew; they shall pursue you until you perish.
05重 28:23 The sky over your head shall be bronze, and the earth under you iron.
05重 28:24 The LORD will change the rain of your land into powder, and only dust shall come down upon you from the sky until you are destroyed.
05重 28:25 The LORD will cause you to be defeated before your enemies; you shall go out against them one way and flee before them seven ways. You shall become an object of horror to all the kingdoms of the earth.
05重 28:26 Your corpses shall be food for every bird of the air and animal of the earth, and there shall be no one to frighten them away.
05重 28:27 The LORD will afflict you with the boils of Egypt, with ulcers, scurvy, and itch, of which you cannot be healed.
05重 28:28 The LORD will afflict you with madness, blindness, and confusion of mind;
05重 28:29 you shall grope about at noon as blind people grope in darkness, but you shall be unable to find your way; and you shall be continually abused and robbed, without anyone to help.
05重 28:30 You shall become engaged to a woman, but another man shall lie with her. You shall build a house, but not live in it. You shall plant a vineyard, but not enjoy its fruit.
05重 28:31 Your ox shall be butchered before your eyes, but you shall not eat of it. Your donkey shall be stolen in front of you, and shall not be restored to you. Your sheep shall be given to your enemies, without anyone to help you.
05重 28:32 Your sons and daughters shall be given to another people, while you look on; you will strain your eyes looking for them all day but be powerless to do anything.
05重 28:33 A people whom you do not know shall eat up the fruit of your ground and of all your labors; you shall be continually abused and crushed,
05重 28:34 and driven mad by the sight that your eyes shall see.
05重 28:35 The LORD will strike you on the knees and on the legs with grievous boils of which you cannot be healed, from the sole of your foot to the crown of your head.
05重 28:36 The LORD will bring you, and the king whom you set over you, to a nation that neither you nor your ancestors have known, where you shall serve other gods, of wood and stone.
05重 28:37 You shall become an object of horror, a proverb, and a byword among all the peoples where the LORD will lead you.
05重 28:38 You shall carry much seed into the field but shall gather little in, for the locust shall consume it.
05重 28:39 You shall plant vineyards and dress them, but you shall neither drink the wine nor gather the grapes, for the worm shall eat them.
05重 28:40 You shall have olive trees throughout all your territory, but you shall not anoint yourself with the oil, for your olives shall drop off.
05重 28:41 You shall have sons and daughters, but they shall not remain yours, for they shall go into captivity.
05重 28:42 All your trees and the fruit of your ground the cicada shall take over.
05重 28:43 Aliens residing among you shall ascend above you higher and higher, while you shall descend lower and lower.
05重 28:44 They shall lend to you but you shall not lend to them; they shall be the head and you shall be the tail.
05重 28:45 All these curses shall come upon you, pursuing and overtaking you until you are destroyed, because you did not obey the LORD your God, by observing the commandments and the decrees that he commanded you.
05重 28:46 They shall be among you and your descendants as a sign and a portent forever.
05重 28:47 Because you did not serve the LORD your God joyfully and with gladness of heart for the abundance of everything,
05重 28:48 therefore you shall serve your enemies whom the LORD will send against you, in hunger and thirst, in nakedness and lack of everything. He will put an iron yoke on your neck until he has destroyed you.
05重 28:49 The LORD will bring a nation from far away, from the end of the earth, to swoop down on you like an eagle, a nation whose language you do not understand,
05重 28:50 a grim-faced nation showing no respect to the old or favor to the young.
05重 28:51 It shall consume the fruit of your livestock and the fruit of your ground until you are destroyed, leaving you neither grain, wine, and oil, nor the increase of your cattle and the issue of your flock, until it has made you perish.
05重 28:52 It shall besiege you in all your towns until your high and fortified walls, in which you trusted, come down throughout your land; it shall besiege you in all your towns throughout the land that the LORD your God has given you.
05重 28:53 In the desperate straits to which the enemy siege reduces you, you will eat the fruit of your womb, the flesh of your own sons and daughters whom the LORD your God has given you.
05重 28:54 Even the most refined and gentle of men among you will begrudge food to his own brother, to the wife whom he embraces, and to the last of his remaining children,
05重 28:55 giving to none of them any of the flesh of his children whom he is eating, because nothing else remains to him, in the desperate straits to which the enemy siege will reduce you in all your towns.
05重 28:56 She who is the most refined and gentle among you, so gentle and refined that she does not venture to set the sole of her foot on the ground, will begrudge food to the husband whom she embraces, to her own son, and to her own daughter,
05重 28:57 begrudging even the afterbirth that comes out from between her thighs, and the children that she bears, because she is eating them in secret for lack of anything else, in the desperate straits to which the enemy siege will reduce you in your towns.
05重 28:58 If you do not diligently observe all the words of this law that are written in this book, fearing this glorious and awesome name, the LORD your God,
05重 28:59 then the LORD will overwhelm both you and your offspring with severe and lasting afflictions and grievous and lasting maladies.
05重 28:60 He will bring back upon you all the diseases of Egypt, of which you were in dread, and they shall cling to you.
05重 28:61 Every other malady and affliction, even though not recorded in the book of this law, the LORD will inflict on you until you are destroyed.
05重 28:62 Although once you were as numerous as the stars in heaven, you shall be left few in number, because you did not obey the LORD your God.
05重 28:63 And just as the LORD took delight in making you prosperous and numerous, so the LORD will take delight in bringing you to ruin and destruction; you shall be plucked off the land that you are entering to possess.
05重 28:64 The LORD will scatter you among all peoples, from one end of the earth to the other; and there you shall serve other gods, of wood and stone, which neither you nor your ancestors have known.
05重 28:65 Among those nations you shall find no ease, no resting place for the sole of your foot. There the LORD will give you a trembling heart, failing eyes, and a languishing spirit.
05重 28:66 Your life shall hang in doubt before you; night and day you shall be in dread, with no assurance of your life.
05重 28:67 In the morning you shall say, "If only it were evening!" and at evening you shall say, "If only it were morning!"--because of the dread that your heart shall feel and the sights that your eyes shall see.
05重 28:68 The LORD will bring you back in ships to Egypt, by a route that I promised you would never see again; and there you shall offer yourselves for sale to your enemies as male and female slaves, but there will be no buyer.
05重 29:1 These are the words of the covenant that the LORD commanded Moses to make with the Israelites in the land of Moab, in addition to the covenant that he had made with them at Horeb.
05重 29:2 Moses summoned all Israel and said to them: You have seen all that the LORD did before your eyes in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all his land,
05重 29:3 the great trials that your eyes saw, the signs, and those great wonders.
05重 29:4 But to this day the LORD has not given you a mind to understand, or eyes to see, or ears to hear.
05重 29:5 I have led you forty years in the wilderness. The clothes on your back have not worn out, and the sandals on your feet have not worn out;
05重 29:6 you have not eaten bread, and you have not drunk wine or strong drink--so that you may know that I am the LORD your God.
05重 29:7 When you came to this place, King Sihon of Heshbon and King Og of Bashan came out against us for battle, but we defeated them.
05重 29:8 We took their land and gave it as an inheritance to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh.
05重 29:9 Therefore diligently observe the words of this covenant, in order that you may succeed in everything that you do.
05重 29:10 You stand assembled today, all of you, before the LORD your God--the leaders of your tribes, your elders, and your officials, all the men of Israel,
05重 29:11 your children, your women, and the aliens who are in your camp, both those who cut your wood and those who draw your water--
05重 29:12 to enter into the covenant of the LORD your God, sworn by an oath, which the LORD your God is making with you today;
05重 29:13 in order that he may establish you today as his people, and that he may be your God, as he promised you and as he swore to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.
05重 29:14 I am making this covenant, sworn by an oath, not only with you who stand here with us today before the LORD our God,
05重 29:15 but also with those who are not here with us today.
05重 29:16 You know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we came through the midst of the nations through which you passed.
05重 29:17 You have seen their detestable things, the filthy idols of wood and stone, of silver and gold, that were among them.
05重 29:18 It may be that there is among you a man or woman, or a family or tribe, whose heart is already turning away from the LORD our God to serve the gods of those nations. It may be that there is among you a root sprouting poisonous and bitter growth.
05重 29:19 All who hear the words of this oath and bless themselves, thinking in their hearts, "We are safe even though we go our own stubborn ways" (thus bringing disaster on moist and dry alike)--
05重 29:20 the LORD will be unwilling to pardon them, for the LORD's anger and passion will smoke against them. All the curses written in this book will descend on them, and the LORD will blot out their names from under heaven.
05重 29:21 The LORD will single them out from all the tribes of Israel for calamity, in accordance with all the curses of the covenant written in this book of the law.
05重 29:22 The next generation, your children who rise up after you, as well as the foreigner who comes from a distant country, will see the devastation of that land and the afflictions with which the LORD has afflicted it--
05重 29:23 all its soil burned out by sulfur and salt, nothing planted, nothing sprouting, unable to support any vegetation, like the destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboiim, which the LORD destroyed in his fierce anger--
05重 29:24 they and indeed all the nations will wonder, "Why has the LORD done thus to this land? What caused this great display of anger?"
05重 29:25 They will conclude, "It is because they abandoned the covenant of the LORD, the God of their ancestors, which he made with them when he brought them out of the land of Egypt.
05重 29:26 They turned and served other gods, worshiping them, gods whom they had not known and whom he had not allotted to them;
05重 29:27 so the anger of the LORD was kindled against that land, bringing on it every curse written in this book.
05重 29:28 The LORD uprooted them from their land in anger, fury, and great wrath, and cast them into another land, as is now the case."
05重 29:29 The secret things belong to the LORD our God, but the revealed things belong to us and to our children forever, to observe all the words of this law.
05重 30:1 When all these things have happened to you, the blessings and the curses that I have set before you, if you call them to mind among all the nations where the LORD your God has driven you,
05重 30:2 and return to the LORD your God, and you and your children obey him with all your heart and with all your soul, just as I am commanding you today,
05重 30:3 then the LORD your God will restore your fortunes and have compassion on you, gathering you again from all the peoples among whom the LORD your God has scattered you.
05重 30:4 Even if you are exiled to the ends of the world, from there the LORD your God will gather you, and from there he will bring you back.
05重 30:5 The LORD your God will bring you into the land that your ancestors possessed, and you will possess it; he will make you more prosperous and numerous than your ancestors.
05重 30:6 Moreover, the LORD your God will circumcise your heart and the heart of your descendants, so that you will love the LORD your God with all your heart and with all your soul, in order that you may live.
05重 30:7 The LORD your God will put all these curses on your enemies and on the adversaries who took advantage of you.
05重 30:8 Then you shall again obey the LORD, observing all his commandments that I am commanding you today,
05重 30:9 and the LORD your God will make you abundantly prosperous in all your undertakings, in the fruit of your body, in the fruit of your livestock, and in the fruit of your soil. For the LORD will again take delight in prospering you, just as he delighted in prospering your ancestors,
05重 30:10 when you obey the LORD your God by observing his commandments and decrees that are written in this book of the law, because you turn to the LORD your God with all your heart and with all your soul.
05重 30:11 Surely, this commandment that I am commanding you today is not too hard for you, nor is it too far away.
05重 30:12 It is not in heaven, that you should say, "Who will go up to heaven for us, and get it for us so that we may hear it and observe it?"
05重 30:13 Neither is it beyond the sea, that you should say, "Who will cross to the other side of the sea for us, and get it for us so that we may hear it and observe it?"
05重 30:14 No, the word is very near to you; it is in your mouth and in your heart for you to observe.
05重 30:15 See, I have set before you today life and prosperity, death and adversity.
05重 30:16 If you obey the commandments of the LORD your God that I am commanding you today, by loving the LORD your God, walking in his ways, and observing his commandments, decrees, and ordinances, then you shall live and become numerous, and the LORD your God will bless you in the land that you are entering to possess.
05重 30:17 But if your heart turns away and you do not hear, but are led astray to bow down to other gods and serve them,
05重 30:18 I declare to you today that you shall perish; you shall not live long in the land that you are crossing the Jordan to enter and possess.
05重 30:19 I call heaven and earth to witness against you today that I have set before you life and death, blessings and curses. Choose life so that you and your descendants may live,
05重 30:20 loving the LORD your God, obeying him, and holding fast to him; for that means life to you and length of days, so that you may live in the land that the LORD swore to give to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.
05重 31:1 When Moses had finished speaking all these words to all Israel,
05重 31:2 he said to them: "I am now one hundred twenty years old. I am no longer able to get about, and the LORD has told me, 'You shall not cross over this Jordan.'
05重 31:3 The LORD your God himself will cross over before you. He will destroy these nations before you, and you shall dispossess them. Joshua also will cross over before you, as the LORD promised.
05重 31:4 The LORD will do to them as he did to Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites, and to their land, when he destroyed them.
05重 31:5 The LORD will give them over to you and you shall deal with them in full accord with the command that I have given to you.
05重 31:6 Be strong and bold; have no fear or dread of them, because it is the LORD your God who goes with you; he will not fail you or forsake you."
05重 31:7 Then Moses summoned Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel: "Be strong and bold, for you are the one who will go with this people into the land that the LORD has sworn to their ancestors to give them; and you will put them in possession of it.
05重 31:8 It is the LORD who goes before you. He will be with you; he will not fail you or forsake you. Do not fear or be dismayed."
05重 31:9 Then Moses wrote down this law, and gave it to the priests, the sons of Levi, who carried the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and to all the elders of Israel.
05重 31:10 Moses commanded them: "Every seventh year, in the scheduled year of remission, during the festival of booths,
05重 31:11 when all Israel comes to appear before the LORD your God at the place that he will choose, you shall read this law before all Israel in their hearing.
05重 31:12 Assemble the people--men, women, and children, as well as the aliens residing in your towns--so that they may hear and learn to fear the LORD your God and to observe diligently all the words of this law,
05重 31:13 and so that their children, who have not known it, may hear and learn to fear the LORD your God, as long as you live in the land that you are crossing over the Jordan to possess."
05重 31:14 The LORD said to Moses, "Your time to die is near; call Joshua and present yourselves in the tent of meeting, so that I may commission him." So Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves in the tent of meeting,
05重 31:15 and the LORD appeared at the tent in a pillar of cloud; the pillar of cloud stood at the entrance to the tent.
05重 31:16 The LORD said to Moses, "Soon you will lie down with your ancestors. Then this people will begin to prostitute themselves to the foreign gods in their midst, the gods of the land into which they are going; they will forsake me, breaking my covenant that I have made with them.
05重 31:17 My anger will be kindled against them in that day. I will forsake them and hide my face from them; they will become easy prey, and many terrible troubles will come upon them. In that day they will say, 'Have not these troubles come upon us because our God is not in our midst?'
05重 31:18 On that day I will surely hide my face on account of all the evil they have done by turning to other gods.
05重 31:19 Now therefore write this song, and teach it to the Israelites; put it in their mouths, in order that this song may be a witness for me against the Israelites.
05重 31:20 For when I have brought them into the land flowing with milk and honey, which I promised on oath to their ancestors, and they have eaten their fill and grown fat, they will turn to other gods and serve them, despising me and breaking my covenant.
05重 31:21 And when many terrible troubles come upon them, this song will confront them as a witness, because it will not be lost from the mouths of their descendants. For I know what they are inclined to do even now, before I have brought them into the land that I promised them on oath."
05重 31:22 That very day Moses wrote this song and taught it to the Israelites.
05重 31:23 Then the LORD commissioned Joshua son of Nun and said, "Be strong and bold, for you shall bring the Israelites into the land that I promised them; I will be with you."
05重 31:24 When Moses had finished writing down in a book the words of this law to the very end,
05重 31:25 Moses commanded the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant of the LORD, saying,
05重 31:26 "Take this book of the law and put it beside the ark of the covenant of the LORD your God; let it remain there as a witness against you.
05重 31:27 For I know well how rebellious and stubborn you are. If you already have been so rebellious toward the LORD while I am still alive among you, how much more after my death!
05重 31:28 Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officials, so that I may recite these words in their hearing and call heaven and earth to witness against them.
05重 31:29 For I know that after my death you will surely act corruptly, turning aside from the way that I have commanded you. In time to come trouble will befall you, because you will do what is evil in the sight of the LORD, provoking him to anger through the work of your hands."
05重 31:30 Then Moses recited the words of this song, to the very end, in the hearing of the whole assembly of Israel:
05重 32:1 Give ear, O heavens, and I will speak; let the earth hear the words of my mouth.
05重 32:2 May my teaching drop like the rain, my speech condense like the dew; like gentle rain on grass, like showers on new growth.
05重 32:3 For I will proclaim the name of the LORD; ascribe greatness to our God!
05重 32:4 The Rock, his work is perfect, and all his ways are just. A faithful God, without deceit, just and upright is he;
05重 32:5 yet his degenerate children have dealt falsely with him, a perverse and crooked generation.
05重 32:6 Do you thus repay the LORD, O foolish and senseless people? Is not he your father, who created you, who made you and established you?
05重 32:7 Remember the days of old, consider the years long past; ask your father, and he will inform you; your elders, and they will tell you.
05重 32:8 When the Most High apportioned the nations, when he divided humankind, he fixed the boundaries of the peoples according to the number of the gods;
05重 32:9 the LORD's own portion was his people, Jacob his allotted share.
05重 32:10 He sustained him in a desert land, in a howling wilderness waste; he shielded him, cared for him, guarded him as the apple of his eye.
05重 32:11 As an eagle stirs up its nest, and hovers over its young; as it spreads its wings, takes them up, and bears them aloft on its pinions,
05重 32:12 the LORD alone guided him; no foreign god was with him.
05重 32:13 He set him atop the heights of the land, and fed him with produce of the field; he nursed him with honey from the crags, with oil from flinty rock;
05重 32:14 curds from the herd, and milk from the flock, with fat of lambs and rams; Bashan bulls and goats, together with the choicest wheat--you drank fine wine from the blood of grapes.
05重 32:15 Jacob ate his fill; Jeshurun grew fat, and kicked. You grew fat, bloated, and gorged! He abandoned God who made him, and scoffed at the Rock of his salvation.
05重 32:16 They made him jealous with strange gods, with abhorrent things they provoked him.
05重 32:17 They sacrificed to demons, not God, to deities they had never known, to new ones recently arrived, whom your ancestors had not feared.
05重 32:18 You were unmindful of the Rock that bore you; you forgot the God who gave you birth.
05重 32:19 The LORD saw it, and was jealous he spurned his sons and daughters.
05重 32:20 He said: I will hide my face from them, I will see what their end will be; for they are a perverse generation, children in whom there is no faithfulness.
05重 32:21 They made me jealous with what is no god, provoked me with their idols. So I will make them jealous with what is no people, provoke them with a foolish nation.
05重 32:22 For a fire is kindled by my anger, and burns to the depths of Sheol; it devours the earth and its increase, and sets on fire the foundations of the mountains.
05重 32:23 I will heap disasters upon them, spend my arrows against them:
05重 32:24 wasting hunger, burning consumption, bitter pestilence. The teeth of beasts I will send against them, with venom of things crawling in the dust.
05重 32:25 In the street the sword shall bereave, and in the chambers terror, for young man and woman alike, nursing child and old gray head.
05重 32:26 I thought to scatter them and blot out the memory of them from humankind;
05重 32:27 but I feared provocation by the enemy, for their adversaries might misunderstand and say, "Our hand is triumphant; it was not the LORD who did all this."
05重 32:28 They are a nation void of sense; there is no understanding in them.
05重 32:29 If they were wise, they would understand this; they would discern what the end would be.
05重 32:30 How could one have routed a thousand, and two put a myriad to flight, unless their Rock had sold them, the LORD had given them up?
05重 32:31 Indeed their rock is not like our Rock; our enemies are fools.
05重 32:32 Their vine comes from the vinestock of Sodom, from the vineyards of Gomorrah; their grapes are grapes of poison, their clusters are bitter;
05重 32:33 their wine is the poison of serpents, the cruel venom of asps.
05重 32:34 Is not this laid up in store with me, sealed up in my treasuries?
05重 32:35 Vengeance is mine, and recompense, for the time when their foot shall slip; because the day of their calamity is at hand, their doom comes swiftly.
05重 32:36 Indeed the LORD will vindicate his people, have compassion on his servants, when he sees that their power is gone, neither bond nor free remaining.
05重 32:37 Then he will say: Where are their gods, the rock in which they took refuge,
05重 32:38 who ate the fat of their sacrifices, and drank the wine of their libations? Let them rise up and help you, let them be your protection!
05重 32:39 See now that I, even I, am he; there is no god beside me. I kill and I make alive; I wound and I heal; and no one can deliver from my hand.
05重 32:40 For I lift up my hand to heaven, and swear: As I live forever,
05重 32:41 when I whet my flashing sword, and my hand takes hold on judgment; I will take vengeance on my adversaries, and will repay those who hate me.
05重 32:42 I will make my arrows drunk with blood, and my sword shall devour flesh--with the blood of the slain and the captives, from the long-haired enemy.
05重 32:43 Praise, O heavens, his people, worship him, all you gods! For he will avenge the blood of his children, and take vengeance on his adversaries; he will repay those who hate him, and cleanse the land for his people.
05重 32:44 Moses came and recited all the words of this song in the hearing of the people, he and Joshua son of Nun.
05重 32:45 When Moses had finished reciting all these words to all Israel,
05重 32:46 he said to them: "Take to heart all the words that I am giving in witness against you today; give them as a command to your children, so that they may diligently observe all the words of this law.
05重 32:47 This is no trifling matter for you, but rather your very life; through it you may live long in the land that you are crossing over the Jordan to possess."
05重 32:48 On that very day the LORD addressed Moses as follows:
05重 32:49 "Ascend this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, across from Jericho, and view the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the Israelites for a possession;
05重 32:50 you shall die there on the mountain that you ascend and shall be gathered to your kin, as your brother Aaron died on Mount Hor and was gathered to his kin;
05重 32:51 because both of you broke faith with me among the Israelites at the waters of Meribath-kadesh in the wilderness of Zin, by failing to maintain my holiness among the Israelites.
05重 32:52 Although you may view the land from a distance, you shall not enter it--the land that I am giving to the Israelites."
05重 33:1 This is the blessing with which Moses, the man of God, blessed the Israelites before his death.
05重 33:2 He said: The LORD came from Sinai, and dawned from Seir upon us; he shone forth from Mount Paran. With him were myriads of holy ones; at his right, a host of his own.
05重 33:3 Indeed, O favorite among peoples, all his holy ones were in your charge; they marched at your heels, accepted direction from you.
05重 33:4 Moses charged us with the law, as a possession for the assembly of Jacob.
05重 33:5 There arose a king in Jeshurun, when the leaders of the people assembled--the united tribes of Israel.
05重 33:6 May Reuben live, and not die out, even though his numbers are few.
05重 33:7 And this he said of Judah: O LORD, give heed to Judah, and bring him to his people; strengthen his hands for him, and be a help against his adversaries.
05重 33:8 And of Levi he said: Give to Levi your Thummim, and your Urim to your loyal one, whom you tested at Massah, with whom you contended at the waters of Meribah;
05重 33:9 who said of his father and mother, "I regard them not"; he ignored his kin, and did not acknowledge his children. For they observed your word, and kept your covenant.
05重 33:10 They teach Jacob your ordinances, and Israel your law; they place incense before you, and whole burnt offerings on your altar.
05重 33:11 Bless, O LORD, his substance, and accept the work of his hands; crush the loins of his adversaries, of those that hate him, so that they do not rise again.
05重 33:12 Of Benjamin he said: The beloved of the LORD rests in safety--the High God surrounds him all day long--the beloved rests between his shoulders.
05重 33:13 And of Joseph he said: Blessed by the LORD be his land, with the choice gifts of heaven above, and of the deep that lies beneath;
05重 33:14 with the choice fruits of the sun, and the rich yield of the months;
05重 33:15 with the finest produce of the ancient mountains, and the abundance of the everlasting hills;
05重 33:16 with the choice gifts of the earth and its fullness, and the favor of the one who dwells on Sinai. Let these come on the head of Joseph, on the brow of the prince among his brothers.
05重 33:17 A firstborn bull--majesty is his! His horns are the horns of a wild ox; with them he gores the peoples, driving them to the ends of the earth; such are the myriads of Ephraim, such the thousands of Manasseh.
05重 33:18 And of Zebulun he said: Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going out; and Issachar, in your tents.
05重 33:19 They call peoples to the mountain; there they offer the right sacrifices; for they suck the affluence of the seas and the hidden treasures of the sand.
05重 33:20 And of Gad he said: Blessed be the enlargement of Gad! Gad lives like a lion; he tears at arm and scalp.
05重 33:21 He chose the best for himself, for there a commander's allotment was reserved; he came at the head of the people, he executed the justice of the LORD, and his ordinances for Israel.
05重 33:22 And of Dan he said: Dan is a lion's whelp that leaps forth from Bashan.
05重 33:23 And of Naphtali he said: O Naphtali, sated with favor, full of the blessing of the LORD, possess the west and the south.
05重 33:24 And of Asher he said: Most blessed of sons be Asher; may he be the favorite of his brothers, and may he dip his foot in oil.
05重 33:25 Your bars are iron and bronze; and as your days, so is your strength.
05重 33:26 There is none like God, O Jeshurun, who rides through the heavens to your help, majestic through the skies.
05重 33:27 He subdues the ancient gods, shatters the forces of old; he drove out the enemy before you, and said, "Destroy!"
05重 33:28 So Israel lives in safety, untroubled is Jacob's abode in a land of grain and wine, where the heavens drop down dew.
05重 33:29 Happy are you, O Israel! Who is like you, a people saved by the LORD, the shield of your help, and the sword of your triumph! Your enemies shall come fawning to you, and you shall tread on their backs.
05重 34:1 Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho, and the LORD showed him the whole land: Gilead as far as Dan,
05重 34:2 all Naphtali, the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah as far as the Western Sea,
05重 34:3 the Negeb, and the Plain--that is, the valley of Jericho, the city of palm trees--as far as Zoar.
05重 34:4 The LORD said to him, "This is the land of which I swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, saying, 'I will give it to your descendants'; I have let you see it with your eyes, but you shall not cross over there."
05重 34:5 Then Moses, the servant of the LORD, died there in the land of Moab, at the LORD's command.
05重 34:6 He was buried in a valley in the land of Moab, opposite Beth-peor, but no one knows his burial place to this day.
05重 34:7 Moses was one hundred twenty years old when he died; his sight was unimpaired and his vigor had not abated.
05重 34:8 The Israelites wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days; then the period of mourning for Moses was ended.
05重 34:9 Joshua son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom, because Moses had laid his hands on him; and the Israelites obeyed him, doing as the LORD had commanded Moses.
05重 34:10 Never since has there arisen a prophet in Israel like Moses, whom the LORD knew face to face.
05重 34:11 He was unequaled for all the signs and wonders that the LORD sent him to perform in the land of Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his servants and his entire land,
05重 34:12 and for all the mighty deeds and all the terrifying displays of power that Moses performed in the sight of all Israel.
