06呪 1:1 After the death of Moses the servant of the LORD, the LORD spoke to Joshua son of Nun, Moses' assistant, saying,
06呪 1:2 "My servant Moses is dead. Now proceed to cross the Jordan, you and all this people, into the land that I am giving to them, to the Israelites.
06呪 1:3 Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given to you, as I promised to Moses.
06呪 1:4 From the wilderness and the Lebanon as far as the great river, the river Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites, to the Great Sea in the west shall be your territory.
06呪 1:5 No one shall be able to stand against you all the days of your life. As I was with Moses, so I will be with you; I will not fail you or forsake you.
06呪 1:6 Be strong and courageous; for you shall put this people in possession of the land that I swore to their ancestors to give them.
06呪 1:7 Only be strong and very courageous, being careful to act in accordance with all the law that my servant Moses commanded you; do not turn from it to the right hand or to the left, so that you may be successful wherever you go.
06呪 1:8 This book of the law shall not depart out of your mouth; you shall meditate on it day and night, so that you may be careful to act in accordance with all that is written in it. For then you shall make your way prosperous, and then you shall be successful.
06呪 1:9 I hereby command you: Be strong and courageous; do not be frightened or dismayed, for the LORD your God is with you wherever you go."
06呪 1:10 Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people,
06呪 1:11 "Pass through the camp, and command the people: 'Prepare your provisions; for in three days you are to cross over the Jordan, to go in to take possession of the land that the LORD your God gives you to possess.'"
06呪 1:12 To the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh Joshua said,
06呪 1:13 "Remember the word that Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, saying, 'The LORD your God is providing you a place of rest, and will give you this land.'
06呪 1:14 Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in the land that Moses gave you beyond the Jordan. But all the warriors among you shall cross over armed before your kindred and shall help them,
06呪 1:15 until the LORD gives rest to your kindred as well as to you, and they too take possession of the land that the LORD your God is giving them. Then you shall return to your own land and take possession of it, the land that Moses the servant of the LORD gave you beyond the Jordan to the east."
06呪 1:16 They answered Joshua: "All that you have commanded us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go.
06呪 1:17 Just as we obeyed Moses in all things, so we will obey you. Only may the LORD your God be with you, as he was with Moses!
06呪 1:18 Whoever rebels against your orders and disobeys your words, whatever you command, shall be put to death. Only be strong and courageous."
06呪 2:1 Then Joshua son of Nun sent two men secretly from Shittim as spies, saying, "Go, view the land, especially Jericho." So they went, and entered the house of a prostitute whose name was Rahab, and spent the night there.
06呪 2:2 The king of Jericho was told, "Some Israelites have come here tonight to search out the land."
06呪 2:3 Then the king of Jericho sent orders to Rahab, "Bring out the men who have come to you, who entered your house, for they have come only to search out the whole land."
06呪 2:4 But the woman took the two men and hid them. Then she said, "True, the men came to me, but I did not know where they came from.
06呪 2:5 And when it was time to close the gate at dark, the men went out. Where the men went I do not know. Pursue them quickly, for you can overtake them."
06呪 2:6 She had, however, brought them up to the roof and hidden them with the stalks of flax that she had laid out on the roof.
06呪 2:7 So the men pursued them on the way to the Jordan as far as the fords. As soon as the pursuers had gone out, the gate was shut.
06呪 2:8 Before they went to sleep, she came up to them on the roof
06呪 2:9 and said to the men: "I know that the LORD has given you the land, and that dread of you has fallen on us, and that all the inhabitants of the land melt in fear before you.
06呪 2:10 For we have heard how the LORD dried up the water of the Red Sea before you when you came out of Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of the Amorites that were beyond the Jordan, to Sihon and Og, whom you utterly destroyed.
06呪 2:11 As soon as we heard it, our hearts melted, and there was no courage left in any of us because of you. The LORD your God is indeed God in heaven above and on earth below.
06呪 2:12 Now then, since I have dealt kindly with you, swear to me by the LORD that you in turn will deal kindly with my family. Give me a sign of good faith
06呪 2:13 that you will spare my father and mother, my brothers and sisters, and all who belong to them, and deliver our lives from death."
06呪 2:14 The men said to her, "Our life for yours! If you do not tell this business of ours, then we will deal kindly and faithfully with you when the LORD gives us the land."
06呪 2:15 Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house was on the outer side of the city wall and she resided within the wall itself.
06呪 2:16 She said to them, "Go toward the hill country, so that the pursuers may not come upon you. Hide yourselves there three days, until the pursuers have returned; then afterward you may go your way."
06呪 2:17 The men said to her, "We will be released from this oath that you have made us swear to you
06呪 2:18 if we invade the land and you do not tie this crimson cord in the window through which you let us down, and you do not gather into your house your father and mother, your brothers, and all your family.
06呪 2:19 If any of you go out of the doors of your house into the street, they shall be responsible for their own death, and we shall be innocent; but if a hand is laid upon any who are with you in the house, we shall bear the responsibility for their death.
06呪 2:20 But if you tell this business of ours, then we shall be released from this oath that you made us swear to you."
06呪 2:21 She said, "According to your words, so be it." She sent them away and they departed. Then she tied the crimson cord in the window.
06呪 2:22 They departed and went into the hill country and stayed there three days, until the pursuers returned. The pursuers had searched all along the way and found nothing.
06呪 2:23 Then the two men came down again from the hill country. They crossed over, came to Joshua son of Nun, and told him all that had happened to them.
06呪 2:24 They said to Joshua, "Truly the LORD has given all the land into our hands; moreover all the inhabitants of the land melt in fear before us."
06呪 3:1 Early in the morning Joshua rose and set out from Shittim with all the Israelites, and they came to the Jordan. They camped there before crossing over.
06呪 3:2 At the end of three days the officers went through the camp
06呪 3:3 and commanded the people, "When you see the ark of the covenant of the LORD your God being carried by the levitical priests, then you shall set out from your place. Follow it,
06呪 3:4 so that you may know the way you should go, for you have not passed this way before. Yet there shall be a space between you and it, a distance of about two thousand cubits; do not come any nearer to it."
06呪 3:5 Then Joshua said to the people, "Sanctify yourselves; for tomorrow the LORD will do wonders among you."
06呪 3:6 To the priests Joshua said, "Take up the ark of the covenant, and pass on in front of the people." So they took up the ark of the covenant and went in front of the people.
06呪 3:7 The LORD said to Joshua, "This day I will begin to exalt you in the sight of all Israel, so that they may know that I will be with you as I was with Moses.
06呪 3:8 You are the one who shall command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, 'When you come to the edge of the waters of the Jordan, you shall stand still in the Jordan.'"
06呪 3:9 Joshua then said to the Israelites, "Draw near and hear the words of the LORD your God."
06呪 3:10 Joshua said, "By this you shall know that among you is the living God who without fail will drive out from before you the Canaanites, Hittites, Hivites, Perizzites, Girgashites, Amorites, and Jebusites:
06呪 3:11 the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is going to pass before you into the Jordan.
06呪 3:12 So now select twelve men from the tribes of Israel, one from each tribe.
06呪 3:13 When the soles of the feet of the priests who bear the ark of the LORD, the Lord of all the earth, rest in the waters of the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan flowing from above shall be cut off; they shall stand in a single heap."
06呪 3:14 When the people set out from their tents to cross over the Jordan, the priests bearing the ark of the covenant were in front of the people.
06呪 3:15 Now the Jordan overflows all its banks throughout the time of harvest. So when those who bore the ark had come to the Jordan, and the feet of the priests bearing the ark were dipped in the edge of the water,
06呪 3:16 the waters flowing from above stood still, rising up in a single heap far off at Adam, the city that is beside Zarethan, while those flowing toward the sea of the Arabah, the Dead Sea, were wholly cut off. Then the people crossed over opposite Jericho.
06呪 3:17 While all Israel were crossing over on dry ground, the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the LORD stood on dry ground in the middle of the Jordan, until the entire nation finished crossing over the Jordan.
06呪 4:1 When the entire nation had finished crossing over the Jordan, the LORD said to Joshua:
06呪 4:2 "Select twelve men from the people, one from each tribe,
06呪 4:3 and command them, 'Take twelve stones from here out of the middle of the Jordan, from the place where the priests' feet stood, carry them over with you, and lay them down in the place where you camp tonight.'"
06呪 4:4 Then Joshua summoned the twelve men from the Israelites, whom he had appointed, one from each tribe.
06呪 4:5 Joshua said to them, "Pass on before the ark of the LORD your God into the middle of the Jordan, and each of you take up a stone on his shoulder, one for each of the tribes of the Israelites,
06呪 4:6 so that this may be a sign among you. When your children ask in time to come, 'What do those stones mean to you?'
06呪 4:7 then you shall tell them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off in front of the ark of the covenant of the LORD. When it crossed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. So these stones shall be to the Israelites a memorial forever."
06呪 4:8 The Israelites did as Joshua commanded. They took up twelve stones out of the middle of the Jordan, according to the number of the tribes of the Israelites, as the LORD told Joshua, carried them over with them to the place where they camped, and laid them down there.
06呪 4:9 (Joshua set up twelve stones in the middle of the Jordan, in the place where the feet of the priests bearing the ark of the covenant had stood; and they are there to this day.)
06呪 4:10 The priests who bore the ark remained standing in the middle of the Jordan, until everything was finished that the LORD commanded Joshua to tell the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua. The people crossed over in haste.
06呪 4:11 As soon as all the people had finished crossing over, the ark of the LORD, and the priests, crossed over in front of the people.
06呪 4:12 The Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh crossed over armed before the Israelites, as Moses had ordered them.
06呪 4:13 About forty thousand armed for war crossed over before the LORD to the plains of Jericho for battle.
06呪 4:14 On that day the LORD exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and they stood in awe of him, as they had stood in awe of Moses, all the days of his life.
06呪 4:15 The LORD said to Joshua,
06呪 4:16 "Command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, to come up out of the Jordan."
06呪 4:17 Joshua therefore commanded the priests, "Come up out of the Jordan."
06呪 4:18 When the priests bearing the ark of the covenant of the LORD came up from the middle of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests' feet touched dry ground, the waters of the Jordan returned to their place and overflowed all its banks, as before.
06呪 4:19 The people came up out of the Jordan on the tenth day of the first month, and they camped in Gilgal on the east border of Jericho.
06呪 4:20 Those twelve stones, which they had taken out of the Jordan, Joshua set up in Gilgal,
06呪 4:21 saying to the Israelites, "When your children ask their parents in time to come, 'What do these stones mean?'
06呪 4:22 then you shall let your children know, 'Israel crossed over the Jordan here on dry ground.'
06呪 4:23 For the LORD your God dried up the waters of the Jordan for you until you crossed over, as the LORD your God did to the Red Sea, which he dried up for us until we crossed over,
06呪 4:24 so that all the peoples of the earth may know that the hand of the LORD is mighty, and so that you may fear the LORD your God forever."
06呪 5:1 When all the kings of the Amorites beyond the Jordan to the west, and all the kings of the Canaanites by the sea, heard that the LORD had dried up the waters of the Jordan for the Israelites until they had crossed over, their hearts melted, and there was no longer any spirit in them, because of the Israelites.
06呪 5:2 At that time the LORD said to Joshua, "Make flint knives and circumcise the Israelites a second time."
06呪 5:3 So Joshua made flint knives, and circumcised the Israelites at Gibeath-haaraloth.
06呪 5:4 This is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: all the males of the people who came out of Egypt, all the warriors, had died during the journey through the wilderness after they had come out of Egypt.
06呪 5:5 Although all the people who came out had been circumcised, yet all the people born on the journey through the wilderness after they had come out of Egypt had not been circumcised.
06呪 5:6 For the Israelites traveled forty years in the wilderness, until all the nation, the warriors who came out of Egypt, perished, not having listened to the voice of the LORD. To them the LORD swore that he would not let them see the land that he had sworn to their ancestors to give us, a land flowing with milk and honey.
06呪 5:7 So it was their children, whom he raised up in their place, that Joshua circumcised; for they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised on the way.
06呪 5:8 When the circumcising of all the nation was done, they remained in their places in the camp until they were healed.
06呪 5:9 The LORD said to Joshua, "Today I have rolled away from you the disgrace of Egypt." And so that place is called Gilgal to this day.
06呪 5:10 While the Israelites were camped in Gilgal they kept the passover in the evening on the fourteenth day of the month in the plains of Jericho.
06呪 5:11 On the day after the passover, on that very day, they ate the produce of the land, unleavened cakes and parched grain.
06呪 5:12 The manna ceased on the day they ate the produce of the land, and the Israelites no longer had manna; they ate the crops of the land of Canaan that year.
06呪 5:13 Once when Joshua was by Jericho, he looked up and saw a man standing before him with a drawn sword in his hand. Joshua went to him and said to him, "Are you one of us, or one of our adversaries?"
06呪 5:14 He replied, "Neither; but as commander of the army of the LORD I have now come." And Joshua fell on his face to the earth and worshiped, and he said to him, "What do you command your servant, my lord?"
06呪 5:15 The commander of the army of the LORD said to Joshua, "Remove the sandals from your feet, for the place where you stand is holy." And Joshua did so.
06呪 6:1 Now Jericho was shut up inside and out because of the Israelites; no one came out and no one went in.
06呪 6:2 The LORD said to Joshua, "See, I have handed Jericho over to you, along with its king and soldiers.
06呪 6:3 You shall march around the city, all the warriors circling the city once. Thus you shall do for six days,
06呪 6:4 with seven priests bearing seven trumpets of rams' horns before the ark. On the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times, the priests blowing the trumpets.
06呪 6:5 When they make a long blast with the ram's horn, as soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then all the people shall shout with a great shout; and the wall of the city will fall down flat, and all the people shall charge straight ahead."
06呪 6:6 So Joshua son of Nun summoned the priests and said to them, "Take up the ark of the covenant, and have seven priests carry seven trumpets of rams' horns in front of the ark of the LORD."
06呪 6:7 To the people he said, "Go forward and march around the city; have the armed men pass on before the ark of the LORD."
06呪 6:8 As Joshua had commanded the people, the seven priests carrying the seven trumpets of rams' horns before the LORD went forward, blowing the trumpets, with the ark of the covenant of the LORD following them.
06呪 6:9 And the armed men went before the priests who blew the trumpets; the rear guard came after the ark, while the trumpets blew continually.
06呪 6:10 To the people Joshua gave this command: "You shall not shout or let your voice be heard, nor shall you utter a word, until the day I tell you to shout. Then you shall shout."
06呪 6:11 So the ark of the LORD went around the city, circling it once; and they came into the camp, and spent the night in the camp.
06呪 6:12 Then Joshua rose early in the morning, and the priests took up the ark of the LORD.
06呪 6:13 The seven priests carrying the seven trumpets of rams' horns before the ark of the LORD passed on, blowing the trumpets continually. The armed men went before them, and the rear guard came after the ark of the LORD, while the trumpets blew continually.
06呪 6:14 On the second day they marched around the city once and then returned to the camp. They did this for six days.
06呪 6:15 On the seventh day they rose early, at dawn, and marched around the city in the same manner seven times. It was only on that day that they marched around the city seven times.
06呪 6:16 And at the seventh time, when the priests had blown the trumpets, Joshua said to the people, "Shout! For the LORD has given you the city.
06呪 6:17 The city and all that is in it shall be devoted to the LORD for destruction. Only Rahab the prostitute and all who are with her in her house shall live because she hid the messengers we sent.
06呪 6:18 As for you, keep away from the things devoted to destruction, so as not to covet and take any of the devoted things and make the camp of Israel an object for destruction, bringing trouble upon it.
06呪 6:19 But all silver and gold, and vessels of bronze and iron, are sacred to the LORD; they shall go into the treasury of the LORD."
06呪 6:20 So the people shouted, and the trumpets were blown. As soon as the people heard the sound of the trumpets, they raised a great shout, and the wall fell down flat; so the people charged straight ahead into the city and captured it.
06呪 6:21 Then they devoted to destruction by the edge of the sword all in the city, both men and women, young and old, oxen, sheep, and donkeys.
06呪 6:22 Joshua said to the two men who had spied out the land, "Go into the prostitute's house, and bring the woman out of it and all who belong to her, as you swore to her."
06呪 6:23 So the young men who had been spies went in and brought Rahab out, along with her father, her mother, her brothers, and all who belonged to her--they brought all her kindred out--and set them outside the camp of Israel.
06呪 6:24 They burned down the city, and everything in it; only the silver and gold, and the vessels of bronze and iron, they put into the treasury of the house of the LORD.
06呪 6:25 But Rahab the prostitute, with her family and all who belonged to her, Joshua spared. Her family has lived in Israel ever since. For she hid the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho.
06呪 6:26 Joshua then pronounced this oath, saying, "Cursed before the LORD be anyone who tries to build this city--this Jericho! At the cost of his firstborn he shall lay its foundation, and at the cost of his youngest he shall set up its gates!"
06呪 6:27 So the LORD was with Joshua; and his fame was in all the land.
06呪 7:1 But the Israelites broke faith in regard to the devoted things: Achan son of Carmi son of Zabdi son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, took some of the devoted things; and the anger of the LORD burned against the Israelites.
06呪 7:2 Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is near Beth-aven, east of Bethel, and said to them, "Go up and spy out the land." And the men went up and spied out Ai.
06呪 7:3 Then they returned to Joshua and said to him, "Not all the people need go up; about two or three thousand men should go up and attack Ai. Since they are so few, do not make the whole people toil up there."
06呪 7:4 So about three thousand of the people went up there; and they fled before the men of Ai.
06呪 7:5 The men of Ai killed about thirty-six of them, chasing them from outside the gate as far as Shebarim and killing them on the slope. The hearts of the people melted and turned to water.
06呪 7:6 Then Joshua tore his clothes, and fell to the ground on his face before the ark of the LORD until the evening, he and the elders of Israel; and they put dust on their heads.
06呪 7:7 Joshua said, "Ah, Lord GOD! Why have you brought this people across the Jordan at all, to hand us over to the Amorites so as to destroy us? Would that we had been content to settle beyond the Jordan!
06呪 7:8 O Lord, what can I say, now that Israel has turned their backs to their enemies!
06呪 7:9 The Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear of it, and surround us, and cut off our name from the earth. Then what will you do for your great name?"
06呪 7:10 The LORD said to Joshua, "Stand up! Why have you fallen upon your face?
06呪 7:11 Israel has sinned; they have transgressed my covenant that I imposed on them. They have taken some of the devoted things; they have stolen, they have acted deceitfully, and they have put them among their own belongings.
06呪 7:12 Therefore the Israelites are unable to stand before their enemies; they turn their backs to their enemies, because they have become a thing devoted for destruction themselves. I will be with you no more, unless you destroy the devoted things from among you.
06呪 7:13 Proceed to sanctify the people, and say, 'Sanctify yourselves for tomorrow; for thus says the LORD, the God of Israel, "There are devoted things among you, O Israel; you will be unable to stand before your enemies until you take away the devoted things from among you."
06呪 7:14 In the morning therefore you shall come forward tribe by tribe. The tribe that the LORD takes shall come near by clans, the clan that the LORD takes shall come near by households, and the household that the LORD takes shall come near one by one.
06呪 7:15 And the one who is taken as having the devoted things shall be burned with fire, together with all that he has, for having transgressed the covenant of the LORD, and for having done an outrageous thing in Israel.'"
06呪 7:16 So Joshua rose early in the morning, and brought Israel near tribe by tribe, and the tribe of Judah was taken.
06呪 7:17 He brought near the clans of Judah, and the clan of the Zerahites was taken; and he brought near the clan of the Zerahites, family by family, and Zabdi was taken.
06呪 7:18 And he brought near his household one by one, and Achan son of Carmi son of Zabdi son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was taken.
06呪 7:19 Then Joshua said to Achan, "My son, give glory to the LORD God of Israel and make confession to him. Tell me now what you have done; do not hide it from me."
06呪 7:20 And Achan answered Joshua, "It is true; I am the one who sinned against the LORD God of Israel. This is what I did:
06呪 7:21 when I saw among the spoil a beautiful mantle from Shinar, and two hundred shekels of silver, and a bar of gold weighing fifty shekels, then I coveted them and took them. They now lie hidden in the ground inside my tent, with the silver underneath."
06呪 7:22 So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and there it was, hidden in his tent with the silver underneath.
06呪 7:23 They took them out of the tent and brought them to Joshua and all the Israelites; and they spread them out before the LORD.
06呪 7:24 Then Joshua and all Israel with him took Achan son of Zerah, with the silver, the mantle, and the bar of gold, with his sons and daughters, with his oxen, donkeys, and sheep, and his tent and all that he had; and they brought them up to the Valley of Achor.
06呪 7:25 Joshua said, "Why did you bring trouble on us? The LORD is bringing trouble on you today." And all Israel stoned him to death; they burned them with fire, cast stones on them,
06呪 7:26 and raised over him a great heap of stones that remains to this day. Then the LORD turned from his burning anger. Therefore that place to this day is called the Valley of Achor.
06呪 8:1 Then the LORD said to Joshua, "Do not fear or be dismayed; take all the fighting men with you, and go up now to Ai. See, I have handed over to you the king of Ai with his people, his city, and his land.
06呪 8:2 You shall do to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho and its king; only its spoil and its livestock you may take as booty for yourselves. Set an ambush against the city, behind it."
06呪 8:3 So Joshua and all the fighting men set out to go up against Ai. Joshua chose thirty thousand warriors and sent them out by night
06呪 8:4 with the command, "You shall lie in ambush against the city, behind it; do not go very far from the city, but all of you stay alert.
06呪 8:5 I and all the people who are with me will approach the city. When they come out against us, as before, we shall flee from them.
06呪 8:6 They will come out after us until we have drawn them away from the city; for they will say, 'They are fleeing from us, as before.' While we flee from them,
06呪 8:7 you shall rise up from the ambush and seize the city; for the LORD your God will give it into your hand.
06呪 8:8 And when you have taken the city, you shall set the city on fire, doing as the LORD has ordered; see, I have commanded you."
06呪 8:9 So Joshua sent them out; and they went to the place of ambush, and lay between Bethel and Ai, to the west of Ai; but Joshua spent that night in the camp.
06呪 8:10 In the morning Joshua rose early and mustered the people, and went up, with the elders of Israel, before the people to Ai.
06呪 8:11 All the fighting men who were with him went up, and drew near before the city, and camped on the north side of Ai, with a ravine between them and Ai.
06呪 8:12 Taking about five thousand men, he set them in ambush between Bethel and Ai, to the west of the city.
06呪 8:13 So they stationed the forces, the main encampment that was north of the city and its rear guard west of the city. But Joshua spent that night in the valley.
06呪 8:14 When the king of Ai saw this, he and all his people, the inhabitants of the city, hurried out early in the morning to the meeting place facing the Arabah to meet Israel in battle; but he did not know that there was an ambush against him behind the city.
06呪 8:15 And Joshua and all Israel made a pretense of being beaten before them, and fled in the direction of the wilderness.
06呪 8:16 So all the people who were in the city were called together to pursue them, and as they pursued Joshua they were drawn away from the city.
06呪 8:17 There was not a man left in Ai or Bethel who did not go out after Israel; they left the city open, and pursued Israel.
06呪 8:18 Then the LORD said to Joshua, "Stretch out the sword that is in your hand toward Ai; for I will give it into your hand." And Joshua stretched out the sword that was in his hand toward the city.
06呪 8:19 As soon as he stretched out his hand, the troops in ambush rose quickly out of their place and rushed forward. They entered the city, took it, and at once set the city on fire.
06呪 8:20 So when the men of Ai looked back, the smoke of the city was rising to the sky. They had no power to flee this way or that, for the people who fled to the wilderness turned back against the pursuers.
06呪 8:21 When Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had taken the city and that the smoke of the city was rising, then they turned back and struck down the men of Ai.
06呪 8:22 And the others came out from the city against them; so they were surrounded by Israelites, some on one side, and some on the other; and Israel struck them down until no one was left who survived or escaped.
06呪 8:23 But the king of Ai was taken alive and brought to Joshua.
06呪 8:24 When Israel had finished slaughtering all the inhabitants of Ai in the open wilderness where they pursued them, and when all of them to the very last had fallen by the edge of the sword, all Israel returned to Ai, and attacked it with the edge of the sword.
06呪 8:25 The total of those who fell that day, both men and women, was twelve thousand--all the people of Ai.
06呪 8:26 For Joshua did not draw back his hand, with which he stretched out the sword, until he had utterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai.
06呪 8:27 Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as their booty, according to the word of the LORD that he had issued to Joshua.
06呪 8:28 So Joshua burned Ai, and made it forever a heap of ruins, as it is to this day.
06呪 8:29 And he hanged the king of Ai on a tree until evening; and at sunset Joshua commanded, and they took his body down from the tree, threw it down at the entrance of the gate of the city, and raised over it a great heap of stones, which stands there to this day.
06呪 8:30 Then Joshua built on Mount Ebal an altar to the LORD, the God of Israel,
06呪 8:31 just as Moses the servant of the LORD had commanded the Israelites, as it is written in the book of the law of Moses, "an altar of unhewn stones, on which no iron tool has been used"; and they offered on it burnt offerings to the LORD, and sacrificed offerings of well-being.
06呪 8:32 And there, in the presence of the Israelites, Joshua wrote on the stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he had written.
06呪 8:33 All Israel, alien as well as citizen, with their elders and officers and their judges, stood on opposite sides of the ark in front of the levitical priests who carried the ark of the covenant of the LORD, half of them in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front of Mount Ebal, as Moses the servant of the LORD had commanded at the first, that they should bless the people of Israel.
06呪 8:34 And afterward he read all the words of the law, blessings and curses, according to all that is written in the book of the law.
06呪 8:35 There was not a word of all that Moses commanded that Joshua did not read before all the assembly of Israel, and the women, and the little ones, and the aliens who resided among them.
06呪 9:1 Now when all the kings who were beyond the Jordan in the hill country and in the lowland all along the coast of the Great Sea toward Lebanon--the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites--heard of this,
06呪 9:2 they gathered together with one accord to fight Joshua and Israel.
06呪 9:3 But when the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Joshua had done to Jericho and to Ai,
06呪 9:4 they on their part acted with cunning: they went and prepared provisions, and took worn-out sacks for their donkeys, and wineskins, worn-out and torn and mended,
06呪 9:5 with worn-out, patched sandals on their feet, and worn-out clothes; and all their provisions were dry and moldy.
06呪 9:6 They went to Joshua in the camp at Gilgal, and said to him and to the Israelites, "We have come from a far country; so now make a treaty with us."
06呪 9:7 But the Israelites said to the Hivites, "Perhaps you live among us; then how can we make a treaty with you?"
06呪 9:8 They said to Joshua, "We are your servants." And Joshua said to them, "Who are you? And where do you come from?"
06呪 9:9 They said to him, "Your servants have come from a very far country, because of the name of the LORD your God; for we have heard a report of him, of all that he did in Egypt,
06呪 9:10 and of all that he did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, King Sihon of Heshbon, and King Og of Bashan who lived in Ashtaroth.
06呪 9:11 So our elders and all the inhabitants of our country said to us, 'Take provisions in your hand for the journey; go to meet them, and say to them, "We are your servants; come now, make a treaty with us."'
06呪 9:12 Here is our bread; it was still warm when we took it from our houses as our food for the journey, on the day we set out to come to you, but now, see, it is dry and moldy;
06呪 9:13 these wineskins were new when we filled them, and see, they are burst; and these garments and sandals of ours are worn out from the very long journey."
06呪 9:14 So the leaders partook of their provisions, and did not ask direction from the LORD.
06呪 9:15 And Joshua made peace with them, guaranteeing their lives by a treaty; and the leaders of the congregation swore an oath to them.
06呪 9:16 But when three days had passed after they had made a treaty with them, they heard that they were their neighbors and were living among them.
06呪 9:17 So the Israelites set out and reached their cities on the third day. Now their cities were Gibeon, Chephirah, Beeroth, and Kiriath-jearim.
06呪 9:18 But the Israelites did not attack them, because the leaders of the congregation had sworn to them by the LORD, the God of Israel. Then all the congregation murmured against the leaders.
06呪 9:19 But all the leaders said to all the congregation, "We have sworn to them by the LORD, the God of Israel, and now we must not touch them.
06呪 9:20 This is what we will do to them: We will let them live, so that wrath may not come upon us, because of the oath that we swore to them."
06呪 9:21 The leaders said to them, "Let them live." So they became hewers of wood and drawers of water for all the congregation, as the leaders had decided concerning them.
06呪 9:22 Joshua summoned them, and said to them, "Why did you deceive us, saying, 'We are very far from you,' while in fact you are living among us?
06呪 9:23 Now therefore you are cursed, and some of you shall always be slaves, hewers of wood and drawers of water for the house of my God."
06呪 9:24 They answered Joshua, "Because it was told to your servants for a certainty that the LORD your God had commanded his servant Moses to give you all the land, and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land before you; so we were in great fear for our lives because of you, and did this thing.
06呪 9:25 And now we are in your hand: do as it seems good and right in your sight to do to us."
06呪 9:26 This is what he did for them: he saved them from the Israelites; and they did not kill them.
06呪 9:27 But on that day Joshua made them hewers of wood and drawers of water for the congregation and for the altar of the LORD, to continue to this day, in the place that he should choose.
06呪 10:1 When King Adoni-zedek of Jerusalem heard how Joshua had taken Ai, and had utterly destroyed it, doing to Ai and its king as he had done to Jericho and its king, and how the inhabitants of Gibeon had made peace with Israel and were among them,
06呪 10:2 he became greatly frightened, because Gibeon was a large city, like one of the royal cities, and was larger than Ai, and all its men were warriors.
06呪 10:3 So King Adoni-zedek of Jerusalem sent a message to King Hoham of Hebron, to King Piram of Jarmuth, to King Japhia of Lachish, and to King Debir of Eglon, saying,
06呪 10:4 "Come up and help me, and let us attack Gibeon; for it has made peace with Joshua and with the Israelites."
06呪 10:5 Then the five kings of the Amorites--the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon--gathered their forces, and went up with all their armies and camped against Gibeon, and made war against it.
06呪 10:6 And the Gibeonites sent to Joshua at the camp in Gilgal, saying, "Do not abandon your servants; come up to us quickly, and save us, and help us; for all the kings of the Amorites who live in the hill country are gathered against us."
06呪 10:7 So Joshua went up from Gilgal, he and all the fighting force with him, all the mighty warriors.
06呪 10:8 The LORD said to Joshua, "Do not fear them, for I have handed them over to you; not one of them shall stand before you."
06呪 10:9 So Joshua came upon them suddenly, having marched up all night from Gilgal.
06呪 10:10 And the LORD threw them into a panic before Israel, who inflicted a great slaughter on them at Gibeon, chased them by the way of the ascent of Beth-horon, and struck them down as far as Azekah and Makkedah.
06呪 10:11 As they fled before Israel, while they were going down the slope of Beth-horon, the LORD threw down huge stones from heaven on them as far as Azekah, and they died; there were more who died because of the hailstones than the Israelites killed with the sword.
06呪 10:12 On the day when the LORD gave the Amorites over to the Israelites, Joshua spoke to the LORD; and he said in the sight of Israel, "Sun, stand still at Gibeon, and Moon, in the valley of Aijalon."
06呪 10:13 And the sun stood still, and the moon stopped, until the nation took vengeance on their enemies. Is this not written in the Book of Jashar? The sun stopped in mid-heaven, and did not hurry to set for about a whole day.
06呪 10:14 There has been no day like it before or since, when the LORD heeded a human voice; for the LORD fought for Israel.
06呪 10:15 Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.
06呪 10:16 Meanwhile, these five kings fled and hid themselves in the cave at Makkedah.
06呪 10:17 And it was told Joshua, "The five kings have been found, hidden in the cave at Makkedah."
06呪 10:18 Joshua said, "Roll large stones against the mouth of the cave, and set men by it to guard them;
06呪 10:19 but do not stay there yourselves; pursue your enemies, and attack them from the rear. Do not let them enter their towns, for the LORD your God has given them into your hand."
06呪 10:20 When Joshua and the Israelites had finished inflicting a very great slaughter on them, until they were wiped out, and when the survivors had entered into the fortified towns,
06呪 10:21 all the people returned safe to Joshua in the camp at Makkedah; no one dared to speak against any of the Israelites.
06呪 10:22 Then Joshua said, "Open the mouth of the cave, and bring those five kings out to me from the cave."
06呪 10:23 They did so, and brought the five kings out to him from the cave, the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon.
06呪 10:24 When they brought the kings out to Joshua, Joshua summoned all the Israelites, and said to the chiefs of the warriors who had gone with him, "Come near, put your feet on the necks of these kings." Then they came near and put their feet on their necks.
06呪 10:25 And Joshua said to them, "Do not be afraid or dismayed; be strong and courageous; for thus the LORD will do to all the enemies against whom you fight."
06呪 10:26 Afterward Joshua struck them down and put them to death, and he hung them on five trees. And they hung on the trees until evening.
06呪 10:27 At sunset Joshua commanded, and they took them down from the trees and threw them into the cave where they had hidden themselves; they set large stones against the mouth of the cave, which remain to this very day.
06呪 10:28 Joshua took Makkedah on that day, and struck it and its king with the edge of the sword; he utterly destroyed every person in it; he left no one remaining. And he did to the king of Makkedah as he had done to the king of Jericho.
06呪 10:29 Then Joshua passed on from Makkedah, and all Israel with him, to Libnah, and fought against Libnah.
06呪 10:30 The LORD gave it also and its king into the hand of Israel; and he struck it with the edge of the sword, and every person in it; he left no one remaining in it; and he did to its king as he had done to the king of Jericho.
06呪 10:31 Next Joshua passed on from Libnah, and all Israel with him, to Lachish, and laid siege to it, and assaulted it.
06呪 10:32 The LORD gave Lachish into the hand of Israel, and he took it on the second day, and struck it with the edge of the sword, and every person in it, as he had done to Libnah.
06呪 10:33 Then King Horam of Gezer came up to help Lachish; and Joshua struck him and his people, leaving him no survivors.
06呪 10:34 From Lachish Joshua passed on with all Israel to Eglon; and they laid siege to it, and assaulted it;
06呪 10:35 and they took it that day, and struck it with the edge of the sword; and every person in it he utterly destroyed that day, as he had done to Lachish.
06呪 10:36 Then Joshua went up with all Israel from Eglon to Hebron; they assaulted it,
06呪 10:37 and took it, and struck it with the edge of the sword, and its king and its towns, and every person in it; he left no one remaining, just as he had done to Eglon, and utterly destroyed it with every person in it.
06呪 10:38 Then Joshua, with all Israel, turned back to Debir and assaulted it,
06呪 10:39 and he took it with its king and all its towns; they struck them with the edge of the sword, and utterly destroyed every person in it; he left no one remaining; just as he had done to Hebron, and, as he had done to Libnah and its king, so he did to Debir and its king.
06呪 10:40 So Joshua defeated the whole land, the hill country and the Negeb and the lowland and the slopes, and all their kings; he left no one remaining, but utterly destroyed all that breathed, as the LORD God of Israel commanded.
06呪 10:41 And Joshua defeated them from Kadesh-barnea to Gaza, and all the country of Goshen, as far as Gibeon.
06呪 10:42 Joshua took all these kings and their land at one time, because the LORD God of Israel fought for Israel.
06呪 10:43 Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.
06呪 11:1 When King Jabin of Hazor heard of this, he sent to King Jobab of Madon, to the king of Shimron, to the king of Achshaph,
06呪 11:2 and to the kings who were in the northern hill country, and in the Arabah south of Chinneroth, and in the lowland, and in Naphoth-dor on the west,
06呪 11:3 to the Canaanites in the east and the west, the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, and the Jebusites in the hill country, and the Hivites under Hermon in the land of Mizpah.
06呪 11:4 They came out, with all their troops, a great army, in number like the sand on the seashore, with very many horses and chariots.
06呪 11:5 All these kings joined their forces, and came and camped together at the waters of Merom, to fight with Israel.
06呪 11:6 And the LORD said to Joshua, "Do not be afraid of them, for tomorrow at this time I will hand over all of them, slain, to Israel; you shall hamstring their horses, and burn their chariots with fire."
06呪 11:7 So Joshua came suddenly upon them with all his fighting force, by the waters of Merom, and fell upon them.
06呪 11:8 And the LORD handed them over to Israel, who attacked them and chased them as far as Great Sidon and Misrephoth-maim, and eastward as far as the valley of Mizpeh. They struck them down, until they had left no one remaining.
06呪 11:9 And Joshua did to them as the LORD commanded him; he hamstrung their horses, and burned their chariots with fire.
06呪 11:10 Joshua turned back at that time, and took Hazor, and struck its king down with the sword. Before that time Hazor was the head of all those kingdoms.
06呪 11:11 And they put to the sword all who were in it, utterly destroying them; there was no one left who breathed, and he burned Hazor with fire.
06呪 11:12 And all the towns of those kings, and all their kings, Joshua took, and struck them with the edge of the sword, utterly destroying them, as Moses the servant of the LORD had commanded.
06呪 11:13 But Israel burned none of the towns that stood on mounds except Hazor, which Joshua did burn.
06呪 11:14 All the spoil of these towns, and the livestock, the Israelites took for their booty; but all the people they struck down with the edge of the sword, until they had destroyed them, and they did not leave any who breathed.
06呪 11:15 As the LORD had commanded his servant Moses, so Moses commanded Joshua, and so Joshua did; he left nothing undone of all that the LORD had commanded Moses.
06呪 11:16 So Joshua took all that land: the hill country and all the Negeb and all the land of Goshen and the lowland and the Arabah and the hill country of Israel and its lowland,
06呪 11:17 from Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir, as far as Baal-gad in the valley of Lebanon below Mount Hermon. He took all their kings, struck them down, and put them to death.
06呪 11:18 Joshua made war a long time with all those kings.
06呪 11:19 There was not a town that made peace with the Israelites, except the Hivites, the inhabitants of Gibeon; all were taken in battle.
06呪 11:20 For it was the LORD's doing to harden their hearts so that they would come against Israel in battle, in order that they might be utterly destroyed, and might receive no mercy, but be exterminated, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
06呪 11:21 At that time Joshua came and wiped out the Anakim from the hill country, from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, and from all the hill country of Judah, and from all the hill country of Israel; Joshua utterly destroyed them with their towns.
06呪 11:22 None of the Anakim was left in the land of the Israelites; some remained only in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod.
06呪 11:23 So Joshua took the whole land, according to all that the LORD had spoken to Moses; and Joshua gave it for an inheritance to Israel according to their tribal allotments. And the land had rest from war.
06呪 12:1 Now these are the kings of the land, whom the Israelites defeated, whose land they occupied beyond the Jordan toward the east, from the Wadi Arnon to Mount Hermon, with all the Arabah eastward:
06呪 12:2 King Sihon of the Amorites who lived at Heshbon, and ruled from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Wadi Arnon, and from the middle of the valley as far as the river Jabbok, the boundary of the Ammonites, that is, half of Gilead,
06呪 12:3 and the Arabah to the Sea of Chinneroth eastward, and in the direction of Beth-jeshimoth, to the sea of the Arabah, the Dead Sea, southward to the foot of the slopes of Pisgah;
06呪 12:4 and King Og of Bashan, one of the last of the Rephaim, who lived at Ashtaroth and at Edrei
06呪 12:5 and ruled over Mount Hermon and Salecah and all Bashan to the boundary of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and over half of Gilead to the boundary of King Sihon of Heshbon.
06呪 12:6 Moses, the servant of the LORD, and the Israelites defeated them; and Moses the servant of the LORD gave their land for a possession to the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh.
06呪 12:7 The following are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the Israelites defeated on the west side of the Jordan, from Baal-gad in the valley of Lebanon to Mount Halak, that rises toward Seir (and Joshua gave their land to the tribes of Israel as a possession according to their allotments,
06呪 12:8 in the hill country, in the lowland, in the Arabah, in the slopes, in the wilderness, and in the Negeb, the land of the Hittites, Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites):
06呪 12:9 the king of Jericho one the king of Ai, which is next to Bethel one
06呪 12:10 the king of Jerusalem one the king of Hebron one
06呪 12:11 the king of Jarmuth one the king of Lachish one
06呪 12:12 the king of Eglon one the king of Gezer one
06呪 12:13 the king of Debir one the king of Geder one
06呪 12:14 the king of Hormah one the king of Arad one
06呪 12:15 the king of Libnah one the king of Adullam one
06呪 12:16 the king of Makkedah one the king of Bethel one
06呪 12:17 the king of Tappuah one the king of Hepher one
06呪 12:18 the king of Aphek one the king of Lasharon one
06呪 12:19 the king of Madon one the king of Hazor one
06呪 12:20 the king of Shimron-meron one the king of Achshaph one
06呪 12:21 the king of Taanach one the king of Megiddo one
06呪 12:22 the king of Kedesh one the king of Jokneam in Carmel one
06呪 12:23 the king of Dor in Naphath-dor one the king of Goiim in Galilee, one
06呪 12:24 the king of Tirzah one thirty-one kings in all.
06呪 13:1 Now Joshua was old and advanced in years; and the LORD said to him, "You are old and advanced in years, and very much of the land still remains to be possessed.
06呪 13:2 This is the land that still remains: all the regions of the Philistines, and all those of the Geshurites
06呪 13:3 (from the Shihor, which is east of Egypt, northward to the boundary of Ekron, it is reckoned as Canaanite; there are five rulers of the Philistines, those of Gaza, Ashdod, Ashkelon, Gath, and Ekron), and those of the Avvim,
06呪 13:4 in the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that belongs to the Sidonians, to Aphek, to the boundary of the Amorites,
06呪 13:5 and the land of the Gebalites, and all Lebanon, toward the east, from Baal-gad below Mount Hermon to Lebo-hamath,
06呪 13:6 all the inhabitants of the hill country from Lebanon to Misrephoth-maim, even all the Sidonians. I will myself drive them out from before the Israelites; only allot the land to Israel for an inheritance, as I have commanded you.
06呪 13:7 Now therefore divide this land for an inheritance to the nine tribes and the half-tribe of Manasseh."
06呪 13:8 With the other half-tribe of Manasseh the Reubenites and the Gadites received their inheritance, which Moses gave them, beyond the Jordan eastward, as Moses the servant of the LORD gave them:
06呪 13:9 from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Wadi Arnon, and the town that is in the middle of the valley, and all the tableland from Medeba as far as Dibon;
06呪 13:10 and all the cities of King Sihon of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, as far as the boundary of the Ammonites;
06呪 13:11 and Gilead, and the region of the Geshurites and Maacathites, and all Mount Hermon, and all Bashan to Salecah;
06呪 13:12 all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and in Edrei (he alone was left of the survivors of the Rephaim); these Moses had defeated and driven out.
06呪 13:13 Yet the Israelites did not drive out the Geshurites or the Maacathites; but Geshur and Maacath live within Israel to this day.
06呪 13:14 To the tribe of Levi alone Moses gave no inheritance; the offerings by fire to the LORD God of Israel are their inheritance, as he said to them.
06呪 13:15 Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of the Reubenites according to their clans.
06呪 13:16 Their territory was from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Wadi Arnon, and the town that is in the middle of the valley, and all the tableland by Medeba;
06呪 13:17 with Heshbon, and all its towns that are in the tableland; Dibon, and Bamoth-baal, and Beth-baal-meon,
06呪 13:18 and Jahaz, and Kedemoth, and Mephaath,
06呪 13:19 and Kiriathaim, and Sibmah, and Zereth-shahar on the hill of the valley,
06呪 13:20 and Beth-peor, and the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth-jeshimoth,
06呪 13:21 that is, all the towns of the tableland, and all the kingdom of King Sihon of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses defeated with the leaders of Midian, Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, as princes of Sihon, who lived in the land.
06呪 13:22 Along with the rest of those they put to death, the Israelites also put to the sword Balaam son of Beor, who practiced divination.
06呪 13:23 And the border of the Reubenites was the Jordan and its banks. This was the inheritance of the Reubenites, according to their families with their towns and villages.
06呪 13:24 Moses gave an inheritance also to the tribe of the Gadites, according to their families.
06呪 13:25 Their territory was Jazer, and all the towns of Gilead, and half the land of the Ammonites, to Aroer, which is east of Rabbah,
06呪 13:26 and from Heshbon to Ramath-mizpeh and Betonim, and from Mahanaim to the territory of Debir,
06呪 13:27 and in the valley Beth-haram, Beth-nimrah, Succoth, and Zaphon, the rest of the kingdom of King Sihon of Heshbon, the Jordan and its banks, as far as the lower end of the Sea of Chinnereth, eastward beyond the Jordan.
06呪 13:28 This is the inheritance of the Gadites according to their clans, with their towns and villages.
06呪 13:29 Moses gave an inheritance to the half-tribe of Manasseh; it was allotted to the half-tribe of the Manassites according to their families.
06呪 13:30 Their territory extended from Mahanaim, through all Bashan, the whole kingdom of King Og of Bashan, and all the settlements of Jair, which are in Bashan, sixty towns,
06呪 13:31 and half of Gilead, and Ashtaroth, and Edrei, the towns of the kingdom of Og in Bashan; these were allotted to the people of Machir son of Manasseh according to their clans--for half the Machirites.
06呪 13:32 These are the inheritances that Moses distributed in the plains of Moab, beyond the Jordan east of Jericho.
06呪 13:33 But to the tribe of Levi Moses gave no inheritance; the LORD God of Israel is their inheritance, as he said to them.
06呪 14:1 These are the inheritances that the Israelites received in the land of Canaan, which the priest Eleazar, and Joshua son of Nun, and the heads of the families of the tribes of the Israelites distributed to them.
06呪 14:2 Their inheritance was by lot, as the LORD had commanded Moses for the nine and one-half tribes.
06呪 14:3 For Moses had given an inheritance to the two and one-half tribes beyond the Jordan; but to the Levites he gave no inheritance among them.
06呪 14:4 For the people of Joseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim; and no portion was given to the Levites in the land, but only towns to live in, with their pasture lands for their flocks and herds.
06呪 14:5 The Israelites did as the LORD commanded Moses; they allotted the land.
06呪 14:6 Then the people of Judah came to Joshua at Gilgal; and Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him, "You know what the LORD said to Moses the man of God in Kadesh-barnea concerning you and me.
06呪 14:7 I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the LORD sent me from Kadesh-barnea to spy out the land; and I brought him an honest report.
06呪 14:8 But my companions who went up with me made the heart of the people melt; yet I wholeheartedly followed the LORD my God.
06呪 14:9 And Moses swore on that day, saying, 'Surely the land on which your foot has trodden shall be an inheritance for you and your children forever, because you have wholeheartedly followed the LORD my God.'
06呪 14:10 And now, as you see, the LORD has kept me alive, as he said, these forty-five years since the time that the LORD spoke this word to Moses, while Israel was journeying through the wilderness; and here I am today, eighty-five years old.
06呪 14:11 I am still as strong today as I was on the day that Moses sent me; my strength now is as my strength was then, for war, and for going and coming.
06呪 14:12 So now give me this hill country of which the LORD spoke on that day; for you heard on that day how the Anakim were there, with great fortified cities; it may be that the LORD will be with me, and I shall drive them out, as the LORD said."
06呪 14:13 Then Joshua blessed him, and gave Hebron to Caleb son of Jephunneh for an inheritance.
06呪 14:14 So Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite to this day, because he wholeheartedly followed the LORD, the God of Israel.
06呪 14:15 Now the name of Hebron formerly was Kiriath-arba; this Arba was the greatest man among the Anakim. And the land had rest from war.
06呪 15:1 The lot for the tribe of the people of Judah according to their families reached southward to the boundary of Edom, to the wilderness of Zin at the farthest south.
06呪 15:2 And their south boundary ran from the end of the Dead Sea, from the bay that faces southward;
06呪 15:3 it goes out southward of the ascent of Akrabbim, passes along to Zin, and goes up south of Kadesh-barnea, along by Hezron, up to Addar, makes a turn to Karka,
06呪 15:4 passes along to Azmon, goes out by the Wadi of Egypt, and comes to its end at the sea. This shall be your south boundary.
06呪 15:5 And the east boundary is the Dead Sea, to the mouth of the Jordan. And the boundary on the north side runs from the bay of the sea at the mouth of the Jordan;
06呪 15:6 and the boundary goes up to Beth-hoglah, and passes along north of Beth-arabah; and the boundary goes up to the Stone of Bohan, Reuben's son;
06呪 15:7 and the boundary goes up to Debir from the Valley of Achor, and so northward, turning toward Gilgal, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, which is on the south side of the valley; and the boundary passes along to the waters of En-shemesh, and ends at En-rogel;
06呪 15:8 then the boundary goes up by the valley of the son of Hinnom at the southern slope of the Jebusites (that is, Jerusalem); and the boundary goes up to the top of the mountain that lies over against the valley of Hinnom, on the west, at the northern end of the valley of Rephaim;
06呪 15:9 then the boundary extends from the top of the mountain to the spring of the Waters of Nephtoah, and from there to the towns of Mount Ephron; then the boundary bends around to Baalah (that is, Kiriath-jearim);
06呪 15:10 and the boundary circles west of Baalah to Mount Seir, passes along to the northern slope of Mount Jearim (that is, Chesalon), and goes down to Beth-shemesh, and passes along by Timnah;
06呪 15:11 the boundary goes out to the slope of the hill north of Ekron, then the boundary bends around to Shikkeron, and passes along to Mount Baalah, and goes out to Jabneel; then the boundary comes to an end at the sea.
06呪 15:12 And the west boundary was the Mediterranean with its coast. This is the boundary surrounding the people of Judah according to their families.
06呪 15:13 According to the commandment of the LORD to Joshua, he gave to Caleb son of Jephunneh a portion among the people of Judah, Kiriath-arba, that is, Hebron (Arba was the father of Anak).
06呪 15:14 And Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak: Sheshai, Ahiman, and Talmai, the descendants of Anak.
06呪 15:15 From there he went up against the inhabitants of Debir; now the name of Debir formerly was Kiriath-sepher.
06呪 15:16 And Caleb said, "Whoever attacks Kiriath-sepher and takes it, to him I will give my daughter Achsah as wife."
06呪 15:17 Othniel son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it; and he gave him his daughter Achsah as wife.
06呪 15:18 When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field. As she dismounted from her donkey, Caleb said to her, "What do you wish?"
06呪 15:19 She said to him, "Give me a present; since you have set me in the land of the Negeb, give me springs of water as well." So Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.
06呪 15:20 This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Judah according to their families.
06呪 15:21 The towns belonging to the tribe of the people of Judah in the extreme South, toward the boundary of Edom, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur,
06呪 15:22 Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah,
06呪 15:23 Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan,
06呪 15:24 Ziph, Telem, Bealoth,
06呪 15:25 Hazor-hadattah, Kerioth-hezron (that is, Hazor),
06呪 15:26 Amam, Shema, Moladah,
06呪 15:27 Hazar-gaddah, Heshmon, Beth-pelet,
06呪 15:28 Hazar-shual, Beer-sheba, Biziothiah,
06呪 15:29 Baalah, Iim, Ezem,
06呪 15:30 Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah,
06呪 15:31 Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah,
06呪 15:32 Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: in all, twenty-nine towns, with their villages.
06呪 15:33 And in the Lowland, Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah,
06呪 15:34 Zanoah, En-gannim, Tappuah, Enam,
06呪 15:35 Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah,
06呪 15:36 Shaaraim, Adithaim, Gederah, Gederothaim: fourteen towns with their villages.
06呪 15:37 Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal-gad,
06呪 15:38 Dilan, Mizpeh, Jokthe-el,
06呪 15:39 Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon,
06呪 15:40 Cabbon, Lahmam, Chitlish,
06呪 15:41 Gederoth, Beth-dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteen towns with their villages.
06呪 15:42 Libnah, Ether, Ashan,
06呪 15:43 Iphtah, Ashnah, Nezib,
06呪 15:44 Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine towns with their villages.
06呪 15:45 Ekron, with its dependencies and its villages;
06呪 15:46 from Ekron to the sea, all that were near Ashdod, with their villages.
06呪 15:47 Ashdod, its towns and its villages; Gaza, its towns and its villages; to the Wadi of Egypt, and the Great Sea with its coast.
06呪 15:48 And in the hill country, Shamir, Jattir, Socoh,
06呪 15:49 Dannah, Kiriath-sannah (that is, Debir),
06呪 15:50 Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim,
06呪 15:51 Goshen, Holon, and Giloh: eleven towns with their villages.
06呪 15:52 Arab, Dumah, Eshan,
06呪 15:53 Janim, Beth-tappuah, Aphekah,
