06呪 15:55 Maon, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah,
06呪 15:56 Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah,
06呪 15:57 Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten towns with their villages.
06呪 15:58 Halhul, Beth-zur, Gedor,
06呪 15:59 Maarath, Beth-anoth, and Eltekon: six towns with their villages.
06呪 15:60 Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), and Rabbah: two towns with their villages.
06呪 15:61 In the wilderness, Beth-arabah, Middin, Secacah,
06呪 15:62 Nibshan, the City of Salt, and En-gedi: six towns with their villages.
06呪 15:63 But the people of Judah could not drive out the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem; so the Jebusites live with the people of Judah in Jerusalem to this day.
06呪 16:1 The allotment of the Josephites went from the Jordan by Jericho, east of the waters of Jericho, into the wilderness, going up from Jericho into the hill country to Bethel;
06呪 16:2 then going from Bethel to Luz, it passes along to Ataroth, the territory of the Archites;
06呪 16:3 then it goes down westward to the territory of the Japhletites, as far as the territory of Lower Beth-horon, then to Gezer, and it ends at the sea.
06呪 16:4 The Josephites--Manasseh and Ephraim--received their inheritance.
06呪 16:5 The territory of the Ephraimites by their families was as follows: the boundary of their inheritance on the east was Ataroth-addar as far as Upper Beth-horon,
06呪 16:6 and the boundary goes from there to the sea; on the north is Michmethath; then on the east the boundary makes a turn toward Taanath-shiloh, and passes along beyond it on the east to Janoah,
06呪 16:7 then it goes down from Janoah to Ataroth and to Naarah, and touches Jericho, ending at the Jordan.
06呪 16:8 From Tappuah the boundary goes westward to the Wadi Kanah, and ends at the sea. Such is the inheritance of the tribe of the Ephraimites by their families,
06呪 16:9 together with the towns that were set apart for the Ephraimites within the inheritance of the Manassites, all those towns with their villages.
06呪 16:10 They did not, however, drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer: so the Canaanites have lived within Ephraim to this day but have been made to do forced labor.
06呪 17:1 Then allotment was made to the tribe of Manasseh, for he was the firstborn of Joseph. To Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead, were allotted Gilead and Bashan, because he was a warrior.
06呪 17:2 And allotments were made to the rest of the tribe of Manasseh, by their families, Abiezer, Helek, Asriel, Shechem, Hepher, and Shemida; these were the male descendants of Manasseh son of Joseph, by their families.
06呪 17:3 Now Zelophehad son of Hepher son of Gilead son of Machir son of Manasseh had no sons, but only daughters; and these are the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
06呪 17:4 They came before the priest Eleazar and Joshua son of Nun and the leaders, and said, "The LORD commanded Moses to give us an inheritance along with our male kin." So according to the commandment of the LORD he gave them an inheritance among the kinsmen of their father.
06呪 17:5 Thus there fell to Manasseh ten portions, besides the land of Gilead and Bashan, which is on the other side of the Jordan,
06呪 17:6 because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance along with his sons. The land of Gilead was allotted to the rest of the Manassites.
06呪 17:7 The territory of Manasseh reached from Asher to Michmethath, which is east of Shechem; then the boundary goes along southward to the inhabitants of En-tappuah.
06呪 17:8 The land of Tappuah belonged to Manasseh, but the town of Tappuah on the boundary of Manasseh belonged to the Ephraimites.
06呪 17:9 Then the boundary went down to the Wadi Kanah. The towns here, to the south of the wadi, among the towns of Manasseh, belong to Ephraim. Then the boundary of Manasseh goes along the north side of the wadi and ends at the sea.
06呪 17:10 The land to the south is Ephraim's and that to the north is Manasseh's, with the sea forming its boundary; on the north Asher is reached, and on the east Issachar.
06呪 17:11 Within Issachar and Asher, Manasseh had Beth-shean and its villages, Ibleam and its villages, the inhabitants of Dor and its villages, the inhabitants of En-dor and its villages, the inhabitants of Taanach and its villages, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages (the third is Naphath).
06呪 17:12 Yet the Manassites could not take possession of those towns; but the Canaanites continued to live in that land.
06呪 17:13 But when the Israelites grew strong, they put the Canaanites to forced labor, but did not utterly drive them out.
06呪 17:14 The tribe of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, "Why have you given me but one lot and one portion as an inheritance, since we are a numerous people, whom all along the LORD has blessed?"
06呪 17:15 And Joshua said to them, "If you are a numerous people, go up to the forest, and clear ground there for yourselves in the land of the Perizzites and the Rephaim, since the hill country of Ephraim is too narrow for you."
06呪 17:16 The tribe of Joseph said, "The hill country is not enough for us; yet all the Canaanites who live in the plain have chariots of iron, both those in Beth-shean and its villages and those in the Valley of Jezreel."
06呪 17:17 Then Joshua said to the house of Joseph, to Ephraim and Manasseh, "You are indeed a numerous people, and have great power; you shall not have one lot only,
06呪 17:18 but the hill country shall be yours, for though it is a forest, you shall clear it and possess it to its farthest borders; for you shall drive out the Canaanites, though they have chariots of iron, and though they are strong."
06呪 18:1 Then the whole congregation of the Israelites assembled at Shiloh, and set up the tent of meeting there. The land lay subdued before them.
06呪 18:2 There remained among the Israelites seven tribes whose inheritance had not yet been apportioned.
06呪 18:3 So Joshua said to the Israelites, "How long will you be slack about going in and taking possession of the land that the LORD, the God of your ancestors, has given you?
06呪 18:4 Provide three men from each tribe, and I will send them out that they may begin to go throughout the land, writing a description of it with a view to their inheritances. Then come back to me.
06呪 18:5 They shall divide it into seven portions, Judah continuing in its territory on the south, and the house of Joseph in their territory on the north.
06呪 18:6 You shall describe the land in seven divisions and bring the description here to me; and I will cast lots for you here before the LORD our God.
06呪 18:7 The Levites have no portion among you, for the priesthood of the LORD is their heritage; and Gad and Reuben and the half-tribe of Manasseh have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan eastward, which Moses the servant of the LORD gave them."
06呪 18:8 So the men started on their way; and Joshua charged those who went to write the description of the land, saying, "Go throughout the land and write a description of it, and come back to me; and I will cast lots for you here before the LORD in Shiloh."
06呪 18:9 So the men went and traversed the land and set down in a book a description of it by towns in seven divisions; then they came back to Joshua in the camp at Shiloh,
06呪 18:10 and Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the LORD; and there Joshua apportioned the land to the Israelites, to each a portion.
06呪 18:11 The lot of the tribe of Benjamin according to its families came up, and the territory allotted to it fell between the tribe of Judah and the tribe of Joseph.
06呪 18:12 On the north side their boundary began at the Jordan; then the boundary goes up to the slope of Jericho on the north, then up through the hill country westward; and it ends at the wilderness of Beth-aven.
06呪 18:13 From there the boundary passes along southward in the direction of Luz, to the slope of Luz (that is, Bethel), then the boundary goes down to Ataroth-addar, on the mountain that lies south of Lower Beth-horon.
06呪 18:14 Then the boundary goes in another direction, turning on the western side southward from the mountain that lies to the south, opposite Beth-horon, and it ends at Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), a town belonging to the tribe of Judah. This forms the western side.
06呪 18:15 The southern side begins at the outskirts of Kiriath-jearim; and the boundary goes from there to Ephron, to the spring of the Waters of Nephtoah;
06呪 18:16 then the boundary goes down to the border of the mountain that overlooks the valley of the son of Hinnom, which is at the north end of the valley of Rephaim; and it then goes down the valley of Hinnom, south of the slope of the Jebusites, and downward to En-rogel;
06呪 18:17 then it bends in a northerly direction going on to En-shemesh, and from there goes to Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim; then it goes down to the Stone of Bohan, Reuben's son;
06呪 18:18 and passing on to the north of the slope of Beth-arabah it goes down to the Arabah;
06呪 18:19 then the boundary passes on to the north of the slope of Beth-hoglah; and the boundary ends at the northern bay of the Dead Sea, at the south end of the Jordan: this is the southern border.
06呪 18:20 The Jordan forms its boundary on the eastern side. This is the inheritance of the tribe of Benjamin, according to its families, boundary by boundary all around.
06呪 18:21 Now the towns of the tribe of Benjamin according to their families were Jericho, Beth-hoglah, Emek-keziz,
06呪 18:22 Beth-arabah, Zemaraim, Bethel,
06呪 18:23 Avvim, Parah, Ophrah,
06呪 18:24 Chephar-ammoni, Ophni, and Geba--twelve towns with their villages:
06呪 18:25 Gibeon, Ramah, Beeroth,
06呪 18:26 Mizpeh, Chephirah, Mozah,
06呪 18:27 Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah,
06呪 18:28 Zela, Haeleph, Jebus (that is, Jerusalem), Gibeah and Kiriath-jearim--fourteen towns with their villages. This is the inheritance of the tribe of Benjamin according to its families.
06呪 19:1 The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of Simeon, according to its families; its inheritance lay within the inheritance of the tribe of Judah.
06呪 19:2 It had for its inheritance Beer-sheba, Sheba, Moladah,
06呪 19:3 Hazar-shual, Balah, Ezem,
06呪 19:4 Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah,
06呪 19:5 Ziklag, Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susah,
06呪 19:6 Beth-lebaoth, and Sharuhen--thirteen towns with their villages;
06呪 19:7 Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan--four towns with their villages;
06呪 19:8 together with all the villages all around these towns as far as Baalath-beer, Ramah of the Negeb. This was the inheritance of the tribe of Simeon according to its families.
06呪 19:9 The inheritance of the tribe of Simeon formed part of the territory of Judah; because the portion of the tribe of Judah was too large for them, the tribe of Simeon obtained an inheritance within their inheritance.
06呪 19:10 The third lot came up for the tribe of Zebulun, according to its families. The boundary of its inheritance reached as far as Sarid;
06呪 19:11 then its boundary goes up westward, and on to Maralah, and touches Dabbesheth, then the wadi that is east of Jokneam;
06呪 19:12 from Sarid it goes in the other direction eastward toward the sunrise to the boundary of Chisloth-tabor; from there it goes to Daberath, then up to Japhia;
06呪 19:13 from there it passes along on the east toward the sunrise to Gath-hepher, to Eth-kazin, and going on to Rimmon it bends toward Neah;
06呪 19:14 then on the north the boundary makes a turn to Hannathon, and it ends at the valley of Iphtah-el;
06呪 19:15 and Kattath, Nahalal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem--twelve towns with their villages.
06呪 19:16 This is the inheritance of the tribe of Zebulun, according to its families--these towns with their villages.
06呪 19:17 The fourth lot came out for Issachar, for the tribe of Issachar, according to its families.
06呪 19:18 Its territory included Jezreel, Chesulloth, Shunem,
06呪 19:19 Hapharaim, Shion, Anaharath,
06呪 19:20 Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez,
06呪 19:21 Remeth, En-gannim, En-haddah, Beth-pazzez;
06呪 19:22 the boundary also touches Tabor, Shahazumah, and Beth-shemesh, and its boundary ends at the Jordan--sixteen towns with their villages.
06呪 19:23 This is the inheritance of the tribe of Issachar, according to its families--the towns with their villages.
06呪 19:24 The fifth lot came out for the tribe of Asher according to its families.
06呪 19:25 Its boundary included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph,
06呪 19:26 Allammelech, Amad, and Mishal; on the west it touches Carmel and Shihor-libnath,
06呪 19:27 then it turns eastward, goes to Beth-dagon, and touches Zebulun and the valley of Iphtah-el northward to Beth-emek and Neiel; then it continues in the north to Cabul,
06呪 19:28 Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, Kanah, as far as Sidon the Great;
06呪 19:29 then the boundary turns to Ramah, reaching to the fortified city of Tyre; then the boundary turns to Hosah, and it ends at the sea; Mahalab, Achzib,
06呪 19:30 Ummah, Aphek, and Rehob--twenty-two towns with their villages.
06呪 19:31 This is the inheritance of the tribe of Asher according to its families--these towns with their villages.
06呪 19:32 The sixth lot came out for the tribe of Naphtali, for the tribe of Naphtali, according to its families.
06呪 19:33 And its boundary ran from Heleph, from the oak in Zaanannim, and Adami-nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum; and it ended at the Jordan;
06呪 19:34 then the boundary turns westward to Aznoth-tabor, and goes from there to Hukkok, touching Zebulun at the south, and Asher on the west, and Judah on the east at the Jordan.
06呪 19:35 The fortified towns are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Chinnereth,
06呪 19:36 Adamah, Ramah, Hazor,
06呪 19:37 Kedesh, Edrei, En-hazor,
06呪 19:38 Iron, Migdal-el, Horem, Beth-anath, and Beth-shemesh--nineteen towns with their villages.
06呪 19:39 This is the inheritance of the tribe of Naphtali according to its families--the towns with their villages.
06呪 19:40 The seventh lot came out for the tribe of Dan, according to its families.
06呪 19:41 The territory of its inheritance included Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir-shemesh,
06呪 19:42 Shaalabbin, Aijalon, Ithlah,
06呪 19:43 Elon, Timnah, Ekron,
06呪 19:44 Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath,
06呪 19:45 Jehud, Bene-berak, Gath-rimmon,
06呪 19:46 Me-jarkon, and Rakkon at the border opposite Joppa.
06呪 19:47 When the territory of the Danites was lost to them, the Danites went up and fought against Leshem, and after capturing it and putting it to the sword, they took possession of it and settled in it, calling Leshem, Dan, after their ancestor Dan.
06呪 19:48 This is the inheritance of the tribe of Dan, according to their families--these towns with their villages.
06呪 19:49 When they had finished distributing the several territories of the land as inheritances, the Israelites gave an inheritance among them to Joshua son of Nun.
06呪 19:50 By command of the LORD they gave him the town that he asked for, Timnath-serah in the hill country of Ephraim; he rebuilt the town, and settled in it.
06呪 19:51 These are the inheritances that the priest Eleazar and Joshua son of Nun and the heads of the families of the tribes of the Israelites distributed by lot at Shiloh before the LORD, at the entrance of the tent of meeting. So they finished dividing the land.
06呪 20:1 Then the LORD spoke to Joshua, saying,
06呪 20:2 "Say to the Israelites, 'Appoint the cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses,
06呪 20:3 so that anyone who kills a person without intent or by mistake may flee there; they shall be for you a refuge from the avenger of blood.
06呪 20:4 The slayer shall flee to one of these cities and shall stand at the entrance of the gate of the city, and explain the case to the elders of that city; then the fugitive shall be taken into the city, and given a place, and shall remain with them.
06呪 20:5 And if the avenger of blood is in pursuit, they shall not give up the slayer, because the neighbor was killed by mistake, there having been no enmity between them before.
06呪 20:6 The slayer shall remain in that city until there is a trial before the congregation, until the death of the one who is high priest at the time: then the slayer may return home, to the town in which the deed was done.'"
06呪 20:7 So they set apart Kedesh in Galilee in the hill country of Naphtali, and Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron) in the hill country of Judah.
06呪 20:8 And beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, they appointed Bezer in the wilderness on the tableland, from the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead, from the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh.
06呪 20:9 These were the cities designated for all the Israelites, and for the aliens residing among them, that anyone who killed a person without intent could flee there, so as not to die by the hand of the avenger of blood, until there was a trial before the congregation.
06呪 21:1 Then the heads of the families of the Levites came to the priest Eleazar and to Joshua son of Nun and to the heads of the families of the tribes of the Israelites;
06呪 21:2 they said to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, "The LORD commanded through Moses that we be given towns to live in, along with their pasture lands for our livestock."
06呪 21:3 So by command of the LORD the Israelites gave to the Levites the following towns and pasture lands out of their inheritance.
06呪 21:4 The lot came out for the families of the Kohathites. So those Levites who were descendants of Aaron the priest received by lot thirteen towns from the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin.
06呪 21:5 The rest of the Kohathites received by lot ten towns from the families of the tribe of Ephraim, from the tribe of Dan, and the half-tribe of Manasseh.
06呪 21:6 The Gershonites received by lot thirteen towns from the families of the tribe of Issachar, from the tribe of Asher, from the tribe of Naphtali, and from the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan.
06呪 21:7 The Merarites according to their families received twelve towns from the tribe of Reuben, the tribe of Gad, and the tribe of Zebulun.
06呪 21:8 These towns and their pasture lands the Israelites gave by lot to the Levites, as the LORD had commanded through Moses.
06呪 21:9 Out of the tribe of Judah and the tribe of Simeon they gave the following towns mentioned by name,
06呪 21:10 which went to the descendants of Aaron, one of the families of the Kohathites who belonged to the Levites, since the lot fell to them first.
06呪 21:11 They gave them Kiriath-arba (Arba being the father of Anak), that is Hebron, in the hill country of Judah, along with the pasture lands around it.
06呪 21:12 But the fields of the town and its villages had been given to Caleb son of Jephunneh as his holding.
06呪 21:13 To the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron, the city of refuge for the slayer, with its pasture lands, Libnah with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:14 Jattir with its pasture lands, Eshtemoa with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:15 Holon with its pasture lands, Debir with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:16 Ain with its pasture lands, Juttah with its pasture lands, and Beth-shemesh with its pasture lands--nine towns out of these two tribes.
06呪 21:17 Out of the tribe of Benjamin: Gibeon with its pasture lands, Geba with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:18 Anathoth with its pasture lands, and Almon with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:19 The towns of the descendants of Aaron--the priests--were thirteen in all, with their pasture lands.
06呪 21:20 As to the rest of the Kohathites belonging to the Kohathite families of the Levites, the towns allotted to them were out of the tribe of Ephraim.
06呪 21:21 To them were given Shechem, the city of refuge for the slayer, with its pasture lands in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:22 Kibzaim with its pasture lands, and Beth-horon with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:23 Out of the tribe of Dan: Elteke with its pasture lands, Gibbethon with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:24 Aijalon with its pasture lands, Gath-rimmon with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:25 Out of the half-tribe of Manasseh: Taanach with its pasture lands, and Gath-rimmon with its pasture lands--two towns.
06呪 21:26 The towns of the families of the rest of the Kohathites were ten in all, with their pasture lands.
06呪 21:27 To the Gershonites, one of the families of the Levites, were given out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with its pasture lands, the city of refuge for the slayer, and Beeshterah with its pasture lands--two towns.
06呪 21:28 Out of the tribe of Issachar: Kishion with its pasture lands, Daberath with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:29 Jarmuth with its pasture lands, En-gannim with its pasture lands--four towns;
06呪 21:30 Out of the tribe of Asher: Mishal with its pasture lands, Abdon with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:31 Helkath with its pasture lands, and Rehob with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:32 Out of the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee with its pasture lands, the city of refuge for the slayer, Hammoth-dor with its pasture lands, and Kartan with its pasture lands--three towns.
06呪 21:33 The towns of the several families of the Gershonites were in all thirteen, with their pasture lands.
06呪 21:34 To the rest of the Levites--the Merarite families--were given out of the tribe of Zebulun: Jokneam with its pasture lands, Kartah with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:35 Dimnah with its pasture lands, Nahalal with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:36 Out of the tribe of Reuben: Bezer with its pasture lands, Jahzah with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:37 Kedemoth with its pasture lands, and Mephaath with its pasture lands--four towns.
06呪 21:38 Out of the tribe of Gad: Ramoth in Gilead with its pasture lands, the city of refuge for the slayer, Mahanaim with its pasture lands,
06呪 21:39 Heshbon with its pasture lands, Jazer with its pasture lands--four towns in all.
06呪 21:40 As for the towns of the several Merarite families, that is, the remainder of the families of the Levites, those allotted to them were twelve in all.
06呪 21:41 The towns of the Levites within the holdings of the Israelites were in all forty-eight towns with their pasture lands.
06呪 21:42 Each of these towns had its pasture lands around it; so it was with all these towns.
06呪 21:43 Thus the LORD gave to Israel all the land that he swore to their ancestors that he would give them; and having taken possession of it, they settled there.
06呪 21:44 And the LORD gave them rest on every side just as he had sworn to their ancestors; not one of all their enemies had withstood them, for the LORD had given all their enemies into their hands.
06呪 21:45 Not one of all the good promises that the LORD had made to the house of Israel had failed; all came to pass.
06呪 22:1 Then Joshua summoned the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh,
06呪 22:2 and said to them, "You have observed all that Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, and have obeyed me in all that I have commanded you;
06呪 22:3 you have not forsaken your kindred these many days, down to this day, but have been careful to keep the charge of the LORD your God.
06呪 22:4 And now the LORD your God has given rest to your kindred, as he promised them; therefore turn and go to your tents in the land where your possession lies, which Moses the servant of the LORD gave you on the other side of the Jordan.
06呪 22:5 Take good care to observe the commandment and instruction that Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, to love the LORD your God, to walk in all his ways, to keep his commandments, and to hold fast to him, and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul."
06呪 22:6 So Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their tents.
06呪 22:7 Now to the one half of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession in Bashan; but to the other half Joshua had given a possession beside their fellow Israelites in the land west of the Jordan. And when Joshua sent them away to their tents and blessed them,
06呪 22:8 he said to them, "Go back to your tents with much wealth, and with very much livestock, with silver, gold, bronze, and iron, and with a great quantity of clothing; divide the spoil of your enemies with your kindred."
06呪 22:9 So the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh returned home, parting from the Israelites at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan, to go to the land of Gilead, their own land of which they had taken possession by command of the LORD through Moses.
06呪 22:10 When they came to the region near the Jordan that lies in the land of Canaan, the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh built there an altar by the Jordan, an altar of great size.
06呪 22:11 The Israelites heard that the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh had built an altar at the frontier of the land of Canaan, in the region near the Jordan, on the side that belongs to the Israelites.
06呪 22:12 And when the people of Israel heard of it, the whole assembly of the Israelites gathered at Shiloh, to make war against them.
06呪 22:13 Then the Israelites sent the priest Phinehas son of Eleazar to the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead,
06呪 22:14 and with him ten chiefs, one from each of the tribal families of Israel, every one of them the head of a family among the clans of Israel.
06呪 22:15 They came to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, and they said to them,
06呪 22:16 "Thus says the whole congregation of the LORD, 'What is this treachery that you have committed against the God of Israel in turning away today from following the LORD, by building yourselves an altar today in rebellion against the LORD?
06呪 22:17 Have we not had enough of the sin at Peor from which even yet we have not cleansed ourselves, and for which a plague came upon the congregation of the LORD,
06呪 22:18 that you must turn away today from following the LORD! If you rebel against the LORD today, he will be angry with the whole congregation of Israel tomorrow.
06呪 22:19 But now, if your land is unclean, cross over into the LORD's land where the LORD's tabernacle now stands, and take for yourselves a possession among us; only do not rebel against the LORD, or rebel against us by building yourselves an altar other than the altar of the LORD our God.
06呪 22:20 Did not Achan son of Zerah break faith in the matter of the devoted things, and wrath fell upon all the congregation of Israel? And he did not perish alone for his iniquity!'"
06呪 22:21 Then the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh said in answer to the heads of the families of Israel,
06呪 22:22 "The LORD, God of gods! The LORD, God of gods! He knows; and let Israel itself know! If it was in rebellion or in breach of faith toward the LORD, do not spare us today
06呪 22:23 for building an altar to turn away from following the LORD; or if we did so to offer burnt offerings or grain offerings or offerings of well-being on it, may the LORD himself take vengeance.
06呪 22:24 No! We did it from fear that in time to come your children might say to our children, 'What have you to do with the LORD, the God of Israel?
06呪 22:25 For the LORD has made the Jordan a boundary between us and you, you Reubenites and Gadites; you have no portion in the LORD.' So your children might make our children cease to worship the LORD.
06呪 22:26 Therefore we said, 'Let us now build an altar, not for burnt offering, nor for sacrifice,
06呪 22:27 but to be a witness between us and you, and between the generations after us, that we do perform the service of the LORD in his presence with our burnt offerings and sacrifices and offerings of well-being; so that your children may never say to our children in time to come, "You have no portion in the LORD."'
06呪 22:28 And we thought, If this should be said to us or to our descendants in time to come, we could say, 'Look at this copy of the altar of the LORD, which our ancestors made, not for burnt offerings, nor for sacrifice, but to be a witness between us and you.'
06呪 22:29 Far be it from us that we should rebel against the LORD, and turn away this day from following the LORD by building an altar for burnt offering, grain offering, or sacrifice, other than the altar of the LORD our God that stands before his tabernacle!"
06呪 22:30 When the priest Phinehas and the chiefs of the congregation, the heads of the families of Israel who were with him, heard the words that the Reubenites and the Gadites and the Manassites spoke, they were satisfied.
06呪 22:31 The priest Phinehas son of Eleazar said to the Reubenites and the Gadites and the Manassites, "Today we know that the LORD is among us, because you have not committed this treachery against the LORD; now you have saved the Israelites from the hand of the LORD."
06呪 22:32 Then the priest Phinehas son of Eleazar and the chiefs returned from the Reubenites and the Gadites in the land of Gilead to the land of Canaan, to the Israelites, and brought back word to them.
06呪 22:33 The report pleased the Israelites; and the Israelites blessed God and spoke no more of making war against them, to destroy the land where the Reubenites and the Gadites were settled.
06呪 22:34 The Reubenites and the Gadites called the altar Witness; "For," said they, "it is a witness between us that the LORD is God."
06呪 23:1 A long time afterward, when the LORD had given rest to Israel from all their enemies all around, and Joshua was old and well advanced in years,
06呪 23:2 Joshua summoned all Israel, their elders and heads, their judges and officers, and said to them, "I am now old and well advanced in years;
06呪 23:3 and you have seen all that the LORD your God has done to all these nations for your sake, for it is the LORD your God who has fought for you.
06呪 23:4 I have allotted to you as an inheritance for your tribes those nations that remain, along with all the nations that I have already cut off, from the Jordan to the Great Sea in the west.
06呪 23:5 The LORD your God will push them back before you, and drive them out of your sight; and you shall possess their land, as the LORD your God promised you.
06呪 23:6 Therefore be very steadfast to observe and do all that is written in the book of the law of Moses, turning aside from it neither to the right nor to the left,
06呪 23:7 so that you may not be mixed with these nations left here among you, or make mention of the names of their gods, or swear by them, or serve them, or bow yourselves down to them,
06呪 23:8 but hold fast to the LORD your God, as you have done to this day.
06呪 23:9 For the LORD has driven out before you great and strong nations; and as for you, no one has been able to withstand you to this day.
06呪 23:10 One of you puts to flight a thousand, since it is the LORD your God who fights for you, as he promised you.
06呪 23:11 Be very careful, therefore, to love the LORD your God.
06呪 23:12 For if you turn back, and join the survivors of these nations left here among you, and intermarry with them, so that you marry their women and they yours,
06呪 23:13 know assuredly that the LORD your God will not continue to drive out these nations before you; but they shall be a snare and a trap for you, a scourge on your sides, and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from this good land that the LORD your God has given you.
06呪 23:14 "And now I am about to go the way of all the earth, and you know in your hearts and souls, all of you, that not one thing has failed of all the good things that the LORD your God promised concerning you; all have come to pass for you, not one of them has failed.
06呪 23:15 But just as all the good things that the LORD your God promised concerning you have been fulfilled for you, so the LORD will bring upon you all the bad things, until he has destroyed you from this good land that the LORD your God has given you.
06呪 23:16 If you transgress the covenant of the LORD your God, which he enjoined on you, and go and serve other gods and bow down to them, then the anger of the LORD will be kindled against you, and you shall perish quickly from the good land that he has given to you."
06呪 24:1 Then Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem, and summoned the elders, the heads, the judges, and the officers of Israel; and they presented themselves before God.
06呪 24:2 And Joshua said to all the people, "Thus says the LORD, the God of Israel: Long ago your ancestors--Terah and his sons Abraham and Nahor--lived beyond the Euphrates and served other gods.
06呪 24:3 Then I took your father Abraham from beyond the River and led him through all the land of Canaan and made his offspring many. I gave him Isaac;
06呪 24:4 and to Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau. I gave Esau the hill country of Seir to possess, but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt.
06呪 24:5 Then I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt with what I did in its midst; and afterwards I brought you out.
06呪 24:6 When I brought your ancestors out of Egypt, you came to the sea; and the Egyptians pursued your ancestors with chariots and horsemen to the Red Sea.
06呪 24:7 When they cried out to the LORD, he put darkness between you and the Egyptians, and made the sea come upon them and cover them; and your eyes saw what I did to Egypt. Afterwards you lived in the wilderness a long time.
06呪 24:8 Then I brought you to the land of the Amorites, who lived on the other side of the Jordan; they fought with you, and I handed them over to you, and you took possession of their land, and I destroyed them before you.
06呪 24:9 Then King Balak son of Zippor of Moab, set out to fight against Israel. He sent and invited Balaam son of Beor to curse you,
06呪 24:10 but I would not listen to Balaam; therefore he blessed you; so I rescued you out of his hand.
06呪 24:11 When you went over the Jordan and came to Jericho, the citizens of Jericho fought against you, and also the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites; and I handed them over to you.
06呪 24:12 I sent the hornet ahead of you, which drove out before you the two kings of the Amorites; it was not by your sword or by your bow.
06呪 24:13 I gave you a land on which you had not labored, and towns that you had not built, and you live in them; you eat the fruit of vineyards and oliveyards that you did not plant.
06呪 24:14 "Now therefore revere the LORD, and serve him in sincerity and in faithfulness; put away the gods that your ancestors served beyond the River and in Egypt, and serve the LORD.
06呪 24:15 Now if you are unwilling to serve the LORD, choose this day whom you will serve, whether the gods your ancestors served in the region beyond the River or the gods of the Amorites in whose land you are living; but as for me and my household, we will serve the LORD."
06呪 24:16 Then the people answered, "Far be it from us that we should forsake the LORD to serve other gods;
06呪 24:17 for it is the LORD our God who brought us and our ancestors up from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, and who did those great signs in our sight. He protected us along all the way that we went, and among all the peoples through whom we passed;
06呪 24:18 and the LORD drove out before us all the peoples, the Amorites who lived in the land. Therefore we also will serve the LORD, for he is our God."
06呪 24:19 But Joshua said to the people, "You cannot serve the LORD, for he is a holy God. He is a jealous God; he will not forgive your transgressions or your sins.
06呪 24:20 If you forsake the LORD and serve foreign gods, then he will turn and do you harm, and consume you, after having done you good."
06呪 24:21 And the people said to Joshua, "No, we will serve the LORD!"
06呪 24:22 Then Joshua said to the people, "You are witnesses against yourselves that you have chosen the LORD, to serve him." And they said, "We are witnesses."
06呪 24:23 He said, "Then put away the foreign gods that are among you, and incline your hearts to the LORD, the God of Israel."
06呪 24:24 The people said to Joshua, "The LORD our God we will serve, and him we will obey."
06呪 24:25 So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and made statutes and ordinances for them at Shechem.
06呪 24:26 Joshua wrote these words in the book of the law of God; and he took a large stone, and set it up there under the oak in the sanctuary of the LORD.
06呪 24:27 Joshua said to all the people, "See, this stone shall be a witness against us; for it has heard all the words of the LORD that he spoke to us; therefore it shall be a witness against you, if you deal falsely with your God."
06呪 24:28 So Joshua sent the people away to their inheritances.
06呪 24:29 After these things Joshua son of Nun, the servant of the LORD, died, being one hundred ten years old.
06呪 24:30 They buried him in his own inheritance at Timnath-serah, which is in the hill country of Ephraim, north of Mount Gaash.
06呪 24:31 Israel served the LORD all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua and had known all the work that the LORD did for Israel.
06呪 24:32 The bones of Joseph, which the Israelites had brought up from Egypt, were buried at Shechem, in the portion of ground that Jacob had bought from the children of Hamor, the father of Shechem, for one hundred pieces of money; it became an inheritance of the descendants of Joseph.
06呪 24:33 Eleazar son of Aaron died; and they buried him at Gibeah, the town of his son Phinehas, which had been given him in the hill country of Ephraim.
